description: Do you know what sort of candies you like? Let's go to the library to find out! You might not be the only tourist here!

name: Candy Town - Candy Town Vista
description: At the end of every year, the citizens of Candy Town will vote to dismantle the most successful facility in town, then pack it into Santa's bag to be distributed to children.

name: Candy Town - Dessert Treasure Ship
description: You're leaving on this flight? We'll be waiting for your next visit! Remember! Even if you wake up, you will forever be a part of Candy Town!

name: Old-School Arcade
description: Once known for its wild style and gorgeous graphics, it was an arcade fighting game that brought the hype. "This is the girls' declaration of war. Prepare yourself!"

name: Old-School Rhythm Arcade Machine
description: Made famous by its simple gameplay and its excellent music, this arcade machine once led the wave of rhythm games among humans. "From L to O to V and E, you give the meaning of my life to me."

name: Crystal Ball of Dreams
description: I hope that what she saw, her memories, and her feelings will be relayed to you through this new song, even in this devastated world. "My heart right now... It's Only For You."

name: Elite Adventurer Medal
description: To commemorate the extraordinary adventures of the Commander and T-Dolls of Griffin.

name: Bar Counter Cutout Board
description: Who the hell knows why suddenly everybody wants to experience the job of a bartender. Maybe it's all thanks to some video game? But then again, this could also be a good thing. I don't when this piece of cardboard will turn into a real bar counter, but if it ever does, it'll surely be like Avalon that the idols have written praises about.

name: Lustrous Gold Trophy
description: Standing at the apex, even if there aren't any extraneous substantive rewards, is a reward in and of itself. Why do humans want to conquer the peak? To breathe the thin air up there? Therefore, this shiny little cup holds no more intrinsic value than the representation of the apex.

name: Silver Trophy
description: Silver has always garnered less attention than brass and gold, which is certainly very confusing, as its value is genuine in both its glossiness and its combat power.

name: Brass Trophy
description: Some people think the existence of a third place in a competition is unnecessary, but you've always got to have a dream, right? After all, the only attractive world is the one you haven't entered yet.

name: Seaside Lodge - Changing Room Floor
description: A stone floor is easy to wash but hard to sweep. It's a chore in itself to explain to a robot the difference between patterns and dust.

name: Seaside Lodge - Beach Rug
description: The rippling of the waves has been blown straight by the sea breeze... That's how the designer explained the design.

name: Seaside Lodge - Surfboard Rack
description: Looking cool while surfing can bring much joy to oneself, but failures while surfing can bring even more joy to everyone else.

name: Seaside Lodge - Lounge Food Cabinet
description: Do you want any dessert? You've already survived the toughest period of dieting, so it's now time to take revenge on your fate!

name: Seaside Lodge - Lounge Table
description: You focus solely on the delicious cakes and drinks while ignoring the table that carries these blessings. Everything that exists has a meaning!

name: Seaside Lodge - Beach Wine Cabinet
description: Please practice moderation in drinking while in the company of friends and a deck of cards. The game and the jokes should be moderate as well.

name: Seaside Lodge - Lounge Trolley
description: Listening to the waves while consuming alcohol and CO2 is also a way of life. After all, freedom is when you let yourself go for those few hours.

name: Seaside Lodge - Lounge Changing Room
description: Please remember your own number to avoid any unnecessary conflict. Please do not hammer on the door after closing it.

name: Seaside Lodge - Locker Room
description: Photography and video recording are forbidden within the area, as is taking others' swimwear... Yes, T-Dolls too, especially them due to precedents.

name: Seaside Lodge - Green Leisure Sofa
description: Please clean off the seawater and sand from your skirt before sitting. Sigh, this sofa is already salty enough...

name: Seaside Lodge - Red Leisure Sofa
description: Leather sofas are not suitable for direct contact with wet skin, please cover up your body before resting on it.

name: Seaside Lodge - Changing Room Bench
description: Can be used for many purposes other than sleeping. However, rules are made to be broken!

name: Seaside Lodge - Lounge Wallpaper
description: Did this building have overly lavish wallpaper first or overly ornate chandeliers first? Money really is the root of one's troubles.

name: Seaside Lodge - Lounge Chandelier
description: Is it too extravagant for a lounge? Let's just make the wallpapers more stylish then! ...I really want to try saying that for once.

name: Seaside Lodge - Beach Row Boat
description: You need to overcome many difficulties when rowing this, such as the wind, the waves, and your teammates who aren't really in sync with you.

name: Seaside Lodge - Seaview Window
description: The beautiful holidays are ending, but you've never really left behind what's outside. After all, humans are not tourists to the natural world.

name: Radiant Beach - Beach Floor
description: Deserts and beaches give completely different kinds of feelings to humans. The Creator must be vexed, having to care for such a troublesome species.

name: Radiant Beach - Beach Blanket
description: A blanket emanating the smell of summer. That is to say sunlight, sea breeze, ice cream and sunscreen.

name: Radiant Beach - Beach Parasol
description: To avoid being pranked, please check if there is a mechanism that will snap the parasol shut before using it -- Haha! You got trapped inside!

name: Radiant Beach - Sandcastle
description: The so-called tragedy is to destroy something of value in front of others... What? Everyone's laughing? The highest form of comedy is tragedy after all!

name: Radiant Beach - Iced Drinks and Snacks
description: The biggest difference with normal snacks is that these usually come into contact with your face first instead of your mouth.

name: Radiant Beach - Artificial Coastline
description: For humans, this is a reminder of where the boundary is. Only through this can the last group of sharks and dolphins on Earth be protected.

name: Radiant Beach - Captain Turtle
description: We didn't give it this hat to wear for fun, it's to prevent it from flipping over! It's been ten times already, ten times!

name: Radiant Beach - Beach Chair (Left)
description: An elegant lady knows how to enjoy a holiday by the seaside, whereas idiots would only use this opportunity to horse around in a new location.

name: Radiant Beach - Beach Chair (Right)
description: An elegant lady knows how to enjoy a holiday by the seaside, whereas idiots would only use this opportunity to horse around in a new location.

name: Radiant Beach - Pirate Treasure Ship
description: This shipwreck proves that people are willing to abandon treasure, friendship, and freedom to obtain the world's best napping spot.

name: Radiant Beach - Beach Bath
description: Did you really think that everyone made this to let you enjoy an afternoon nap? They just wanted to bury you and draw on your face!

name: Radiant Beach - Ocean Vista
description: We understand that you want to see more of the ocean, but that's not your home after all... As for who it belongs to, it's best if you don't ask.

name: Radiant Beach - Mysterious Island
description: Do you believe that there's a stupid box there worth abandoning everything for? Or are you satisfied with yourself with the thought that "friendship is the biggest treasure of all"?

name: Radiant Beach - Small Sailboat
description: This kind of small toy boat can only drift near the beach, and you'll need to swim if you want to go further. You are T-Dolls, remember?

name: Radiant Beach - Hot Air Balloon
description: The more of the world you see, the more you'll think of home... Nothing in life is easy, that's why it's interesting, isn't it?

name: Let's go to Seoul! - Vintage Wooden Floor
description: A classical vintage wooden floor. "As I stand on the forgotten station, I put my heart and soul into my bag, and wait for the train that comes only for me."

name: Let's go to Seoul! - Vintage Plaid Rug
description: A traditional rug woven neat and tight. "From L to O and to V and E, you are the meaning of my life."

name: Let's go to Seoul! - Commemorative Snowglobe
description: A snowglobe with the buildings of Seoul within. "That day when the white snow turned into happiness; that day when the white snow turned into laughter."

name: Let's go to Seoul! - Potted Monstera
description: An ornamental plant that improves one's mood. "Let us hold hands as we gaze at the blue sky, and sketch out a world of our creation."

name: Let's go to Seoul! - Souvenir Shelf
description: A shelf with meticulously arranged souvenirs on it. "Buy one shirt less each month and you'll have five goats! Send it as a gift to your friend on the other side of the world!"

name: Let's go to Seoul! - Glass Table
description: A glass table for your own pastime. "With a glass of aromatic red wine and a slice of cake at the end of a tiring day, loneliness creeps up behind your heart."

name: Let's go to Seoul! - Floor Lamp
description: A simple floor lamp. "I close my eyes and think of you. I look for you in my heart, for it was you who let me see the light."

name: Let's go to Seoul! - Telescope
description: A telescope favored by hobbyists. "In the faraway Milky Way, there is a small white boat, and on the boat is an osmanthus tree, where white bunnies frolic and play."

name: Let's go to Seoul! - Korean-Style Dinner Table
description: A traditional Korean-style short-legged dinner table. "Arirang ah Arirang, your road ahead is long and arduous; day and night I think of you, remembering my promise I dwell in this empty house."

name: Let's go to Seoul! - Trendy Curved TV
description: A curved television that was once cutting-edge technology. "I want to build my own world with these two hands. Do not force me to live a life similar to yours."

name: Let's go to Seoul! - Big Sofa
description: A two-person sofa that warms people's hearts. "You would never say goodbye to me, but leave me dumbly sitting there in a daze."

name: Let's go to Seoul! - Korean-Style Cushion
description: A traditional Korean-style cushion. "Three little bears in a house. Papa bear, Mama bear, and Baby bear. What a happy family!"

name: Let's go to Seoul! - Vintage Wallpaper
description: A vintage wallpaper with a solemn feel. "The wind calls out our dying memories as it cries through the ruins. I hope you've gotten used to hugs being farewell."

name: Let's go to Seoul! - Trendy Ceiling Lamp
description: A crystal clear glass lamp. "Your smile is as beautiful as the four corners of the Earth, sparkling brightly like a pure crystal."

name: Let's go to Seoul! - Trendy Floor-to-Ceiling Window
description: A floor-to-ceiling window that lets one admire the night view. "Can I get through all this just as you did? It is like a long and dark night, this I can feel."

name: Hot Spring Time - Japanese Flagstone Path
description: A Japanese-style flooring made of stone. "Even if the journey ahead is full of unknowns, I will still move on ahead happily."

name: Hot Spring Time - Hot Spring Signpost
description: A signpost marking the location of the hot spring. "The beautiful days have long since passed, and homesickness gallops onwards tirelessly; it creeps ever closer and touches my skin, gently guiding my heart."

name: Hot Spring Time - Lantern Rack
description: A lantern rack for lively events. "The small lanterns glowing red bloom cheerfully in the Summer Festival, as the twinkling of the wind chimes reverberate within my mind."

name: Hot Spring Time - Ramen Shop
description: A Japanese-style moving ramen stall. "I wonder what is the taste of wine shared with family; I wonder for whom did you sing for before passing away."

name: Hot Spring Time - Dumpling Shop
description: A Japanese-style moving food stall. "On the round moon in the sky a rabbit waves. Take all your happiness and sadness and knead them together!"

name: Hot Spring Time - Jizo Statues
description: Jizo statues by the roadside. "Embrace the protection of God, share your joy and pain; calmly accept others' happiness, for those who are happy are the most human."

name: Hot Spring Time - Hot Spring Wooden Fence
description: A wooden fence for the hot spring. "The stars shine brightly as the cries of wild ducks fill the air. I bite on a chestnut as I remember father's smile."

name: Hot Spring Time - Hot Spring
description: A traditional hot spring built by hand. "Let us stay at the hot spring hostel tonight, to bathe our sore flesh in the pure water, as cute dancers twirl within the banquet halls."

name: Hot Spring Time - Hot Spring Changing Room Bench
description: A long bench used in changing rooms and restrooms. "As your hair emits a strong fragrance, you who are clad in a bathrobe are incomparably brilliant."

name: Hot Spring Time - Hot Spring Changing Room
description: A small building for changing clothes. "The starry sky, the cloudless moonlit night, unintentionally they trespass into this sealed building."

name: Hot Spring Time - Firefly Bamboo Forest
description: A bamboo forest dotted with fireflies in the distance. "Summer prayers, summer prayers, those are miraculous songs of the fireflies, a tune of wind chimes performed by the wind."

name: Hot Spring Time - Carp Kite
description: A traditional carp kite prepared for the kids. "I'm already tired of baby-sitting, even before the Bon Festival came. The snow began to fall, and the baby cries. "

name: Hot Spring Time - Hot Spring Bamboo
description: An elegant bamboo forest planted by hand. "The moonlight shines down between the trees as I gently caress your cheek, the branches swaying beneath the glistening white moon."

name: Hot Spring Time - Hot Spring Wooden Bathtub
description: A traditional wooden bathtub. "Daily we crowd around the old and worn heater, the whole family happily spending time together."

name: Wine and Refuge - "Glory Album" Floor Tiles
description: A fossil depicting human activities shows that humans wore shoes just like T-Dolls do, and that they also liked to use chewing gum to mark their territory.

name: Wine and Refuge - "Indulgence" Rug
description: In the past, bandits who terrorized cities would be forced to buy this item and pray for redemption on it. They would also take on "von" as a middle name to mark themselves as criminals.

name: Wine and Refuge - "Devil's Operating Table" Bar Counter
description: These small-scale private examination tables can cure many of humanity's mental illnesses, or make them even worse... At least this will stop the problem from being a problem any longer.

name: Wine and Refuge - "More Dangerous Wolf" Motorcycle
description: It is commonly believed that the protests of animal rights' groups caused humans to abandon riding animals and switched to riding on machines instead, thereby greatly increasing the number of deaths by falling.

name: Wine and Refuge - "Old Dog's Nest" Bar Sofa
description: Where should we go to find a dog? It must be loyal, have drooping ears, be friendly around T-Dolls, and hopefully not have gone mad in this forsaken place.

name: Wine and Refuge - "Street Percussion" Pool Table
description: The inability of humans to balance their physical exhaustion and mental enjoyment during their brief periods of rest led to the emergence of this activity, along with the go-soccer club.

name: Wine and Refuge - "Industrial Scale" Storage Rack
description: The Creators liked to measure the value of all kinds of items. They would place all the precious items here, and then never touch them ever again.

name: Wine and Refuge - "Pandora's Box" Supply Boxes
description: Legend says that should this kind of box be opened, a tragedy where everyone tried to kill each other would occur. As for hope... Well, whoever survives is hope.

name: Wine and Refuge - "Simple Recycle Bin" Table
description: Humans like to put their trash on surfaces like this then wait for it to be cleaned by someone else... As for how we know, it's because the trash is still here.

name: Wine and Refuge - "Dwarf Helper" Bar Stool
description: "This tool proves that humans would discriminate against their own based on height, right, shorty?" "Perhaps. Just let me down right now and I might let you live."

name: Wine and Refuge - "Story Prompter" Chair - Left
description: Humans always have endless stories to tell, but who really cares? War can never be stopped because every person thinks of themselves as unfortunate.

name: Wine and Refuge - "Story Prompter" Chair - Right
description: Humans always have endless stories to tell, but who really cares? War can never be stopped because every person thinks of themselves as unfortunate.

name: Wine and Refuge - "Chocolate Frosting" Brick Wall
description: The maturation of humanity seems to be a meaningless thing since they commonly consider being willing to do bad things as "naive" and being afraid to do good things as "mature".

name: Wine and Refuge - "Newbie's Riot Shield" Shooting Target
description: We have reason to believe that this is the prototype of modern shields. It is full of bullet holes and commonly appears in violent situations.

name: Wine and Refuge - "Olive Branch" Lighting
description: To "throw out the olive branch" is an incomprehensible idiom from old newspapers unless we consider to this bent bar an olive branch.

name: Wine and Refuge - "Busy People Forbidden" Safety Door
description: How interesting. Those who come in are always those who are nearly overworked to death, whereas those who don't come... Maybe they don't feel like drinking today. (Shrug)

name: Wine and Refuge - "Humanity's Heritage" Bar Sign
description: These documents express the long-cherished wish of most humans. It is simple and beautiful, but for some reason difficult to realize, even during times of peace.

name: Great Library - Classical Floor
description:
"A scholar may not necessarily possess knowledge. True knowledge is to recognize knowledge, to be able to ruminate on it, to be able to work." 
What...... don't we study because we don't want to work... I'm tired, time for a break...... -- M249

name: Great Library - Library Round Rug
description:
"I leap onto books just like a starving person leaps onto bread."
Yes, I know that feeling, but mine's even stronger. I'll leap even when I'm not hungry, just like this! Bang--! -- FFC

name: Great Library - Bookshelf with Stairs
description:
"Books are the best anesthetic for the soul." -- Quote from AK47
"Some people only absorb the toxins within books." -- Quote from Suomi

name: Great Library - Luxurious Bookshelf
description:
"People who stop studying will stop thinking." -- MP446
People who only read comics all day have already stopped thinking long ago. -- Mosin-Nagant

name: Great Library - Library Reading Stand
description:
"All books are dreams if not blades; you can kill through words, or you can entrance through words."
I've gained a profound insight from this. You can avoid arguing if you just fight. -- Type97S
M99, get someone who isn't hopelessly stupid to read aloud next time. -- Z62

name: Great Library - Library Desk
description:
"The act of learning demands from people the greatest tensions and the greatest enthusiasm."
No, the S.F. do. -- KXG
No, games do! -- RFP

name: Great Library - Classical Lamp
description:
"Books are like a magic lamp, illuminating the longest and dimmest road of one's life."
That's right! When I open an e-book on my tablet, the backlight is great for lighting at night! -- M1873

name: Great Library - Classical Round Table
description:
"Besides barbaric countries, the entire world is ruled by books."
Huh, books couldn't really rule over much then, especially nowadays. -- Negev

name: Great Library - Library Moving Stairs
description:
"Books are stairs of human progress."
No one knows where the stairs will lead... Perhaps we shall see it soon. -- Vector

name: Great Library - Library Sofa Bed
description:
"Reading is to the spirit as what exercise is to the body."
Therefore, both are bad for us. Only the sofa heals the body and spirit. -- F2000

name: Great Library - Library Chair - Right
description:
"Knowledge is power." -- FMS
"Power is justice!" -- Bren Ten
"The winner is justice!" -- SVD
"Cuteness is justice!" -- MkG28
"The three of you, get out." -- P99

name: Great Library - Library Chair - Left
description:
"Knowledge is power." -- FMS
"Power is justice!" -- Bren Ten
"The winner is justice!" -- SVD
"Cuteness is justice!" -- MkG28
"The three of you, get out." -- P99

name: Great Library - Bookshelf Wall
description:
"Books are tools to build up our souls."
Do we even need to read books since we don't have souls? -- Type64
If you need it then read it. -- Type56-1

name: Great Library - Library Fireplace
description:
"Education! Science! To study is to light the torch! We're launching every syllable of every word to Mars!"
Launch to Mars? Are we asking for help from the Martians? Can we ask them to bring food? -- OTs44
The Martians will probably make the situation worse if you've watched movies before... -- OTs14

name: Great Library - Classical Chandelier
description:
"Books are lamps containing mankind's accumulated wisdom."
Hah, based on the statistics of war from the past hundred-odd years, it's obvious that this is referring to the wisdom of self-destruction. -- Ingram

name: Great Library - Classical Governor Portrait
description:
"Books are the president of human knowledge."
Supposedly this is a quote by Shakespeare, but presidents didn't exist during his time... If humans are always correct, then perhaps this is proof that books can send you across time and space. -- Sten

name: Late Night Kitchen - Cooking Floorboard
description: Lee-Enfield: Please do not roller skate in the kitchen, especially while I'm making butter... Shut up and stand still! IDW, please clean up this battlefield after I'm done.

name: Late Night Kitchen - Late Night Kitchen Rug
description:
Gr G36: Here are the ingredients for making grilled sausages. Do you think we're missing anything?
Gr G36C: How about we add some spices? Like...parsley? 
Gr G36: Okay♪ Come and help me.

name: Late Night Kitchen - Giant Roast Turkey
description:
M1873: Hahahaha! I watched that episode of Mr. Nut! So this is how you guys eat turkey!
Bren: Yeah, unlike you guys who eat this every year to celebrate surviving treason.

name: Late Night Kitchen - Cooking Stove
description:
AR70: How's the heat?
SAT8: Al dente!
AR70: Uh...what?
SAT8: Oh, tradition is the essence of my country's dishes, and even the terminology is saved in my neural cloud.
M38: That's...just a common saying...

name: Late Night Kitchen - Cooking Sink
description:
Type81R: T91, I didn't expect you to finish washing dishes this quickly.
T91: I've worked at a tea shop before. You're also pretty quick yourself.
Type81R: Ugh... I've worked on a train before... The "peanuts, beer, and sausages here! Coming through, comrade!" type of work...

name: Late Night Kitchen - Cooking Counter
description:
FMS: AAT, remember next time that this type of bread doesn't need to be scored. You don't need to make any cuts on it.
AAT52: Scored? You mean the cuts aren't made for fun?

name: Late Night Kitchen - Cooking Room Refrigerator
description: Welrod: I'm never opening it in the middle of the night ever again! Bren's sardine pie kept staring at me, and those lampreys that Ribeyrolles added to the pie...they're still alive!

name: Late Night Kitchen - Washing Machine
description:
P7: Ciao, Miss Cutey! Come and order some red wine and bread! It'll make you plump and juicy!
SPAS12: Is that so? I think cola and burgers are good enough for me.
ARX160: (Sigh) Really? I'll have a taste...
P7: Please finish it in one bite, since...it's really troublesome to clean up. (Quietly)

name: Late Night Kitchen - High Stool - Left
description:
M500: Hey, shorty, you're not gonna help?
S-Shorty: No, my hands can't reach the table...
M500: We have a stool right here!
S-Shorty: It's too tall as well... (Sobs)

name: Late Night Kitchen - High Stool - Right
description:
M500: Hey, shorty, you're not gonna help?
S-Shorty: No, my hands can't reach the table...
M500: We have a stool right here!
S-Shorty: It's too tall as well... (Sobs)

name: Late Night Kitchen - Cooking Room Shelves
description:
m45: Eh? Ak5, have you seen the bread that I've just finished baking?
Ak5: I think P7 took it just now along with a can of canned fish... Eh? Why are you laughing? Big sis?

name: Late Night Kitchen - Cooking Utensil Hanging Rack
description:
Type79: Please watch, Miss Cooking Supervisor, we just need to add a little salt, then we can proceed to the next step!
MP40: Little... So how much is that?
Type79: However much you like?
MP40: (Writes on notebook) Type79's language and mathematics module needs to be checked.

name: Late Night Kitchen - Cooking Room Window
description:
PSM: ...What a beautiful night.
T33: Even if there was canned salmon in the bread you ate?
PSM: I thought it was really tasty though. Why did everyone say it was bad?
T33: Uhh...this must be because...everyone wanted to surprise you?

name: Halloween Town - Rotting Nation
description: The rotting weeds wail beneath your feet, but you continue on helplessly, for someone must uncover the secret. What is the secret? The method of your death.

name: Halloween Town - Fogless Stone Path
description: You may think that such a stone path is enough to stop the zombies from breaking out from the ground, but the creeping sounds from beneath the stone tiles may hint at even scarier things.

name: Halloween Town - Dark Forest
description: The flashing shadows and muffled roars make one believe that this is a road of no return, and that the unknown is just as mystifying as death. Perhaps it is better to say that there's no difference between the two.

name: Halloween Town - Fantasy Candy House
description: On it is written "take only one". You have a feeling that the children that disregard the sign will be grabbed by - something - inside the tree.

name: Halloween Town - Bonfire of the Undead
description: You feel alive sitting next to the bonfire. Perhaps your darkness is in search of the flames, drawing you to a path of destruction and obtaining life anew.

name: Halloween Town - Grave Ruins
description: The direction that the tombstone fell in seems to be pointing to a certain place. You don't know what this means, but hopefully it's just a harmless prank.

name: Halloween Town - Unicorn Spirit
description: A unicorn who seems to have a "thin" skin is awaiting your help. With just a whistle, it will bring you to where it wants to go.

name: Halloween Town - Evil Road Sign
description: You can't clearly see what is written on it, but you still touch it anyway. Life is just like that: The less one's burden, the easier their death is.

name: Halloween Town - Slave Fence
description: You hear the sounds of chains being dragged on the other side of the fence, yet you can't see anything. You decide to leave before the sounds approach you, lest you encounter the source of the sounds face to face.

name: Halloween Town - The End of Fear
description: This thing is inviting you to enter and have a drink and relax a bit. Pray that you'll be able to leave before dawn, otherwise hope that you'll simply never wake up.

name: Halloween Town - Bride's Resting Place
description: You hear the whispers of a young girl that lies here, waiting for a certain person's ring to awaken her. Perhaps...ice cream will work as well.

name: Halloween Town - Witch's Bucket
description: You knock on the bucket, and from within a rough voice shouts "lots of buckets here, take your pick!" Maybe next time...in the bar.

name: Halloween Town - Magical Carriage
description: Looking into the carriage, you see that Cinderella isn't inside. There isn't anyone inside at all. You can hide inside if danger comes, assuming that the carriage doesn't eat you first.

name: Halloween Town - Pathway of Exile
description: You've heard before that only criminals would step on this land. They would either lose their life and disappear, or lose their souls and become this place's new master.

name: Halloween Town - Evil Spirit's Castle
description: At long last, the great gates of the city have opened for you. What is it that lies within your heart that will allow you to survive this night? Perhaps this is the answer.

name: Garden Tea Party - Garden House Floor Tiles
description: A soft floor that exudes an atmosphere of calmness. "Soon the paths filled with our footprints will connect together. One day it will become a signal of light guiding one to their future."

name: Garden Tea Party - Miniature Lawn
description: A lawn filled with small little flowers. "The only memories I have are of the footprints when we first met and the fragrant flowers beneath our feet."

name: Garden Tea Party - Garden House Glass Wall
description: A glass wall that is able to keep the bad weather away. "Sunny days, rainy days, cloudy days, doesn't matter what kind of day it is, there are 28 weather forecasters here!"

name: Garden Tea Party - Tea Party Table
description: A table to place desserts and drinks on. "The silver spoon is soaring through the sky, eating the melting moon bite by bite."

name: Garden Tea Party - Short Grass Hedge
description: A meticulously trimmed grass hedge. "I know who you are. You're a high wall that I must cross over, as you want to make me fall and cry."

name: Garden Tea Party - Small Flower Bed
description: A small decorative flower bed. "The birds fly freely through the sky, they will surely understand the song of the wind; the flowers bloom gloriously, they will surely fall into an eternal dream."

name: Garden Tea Party - Blossoming Flowers
description: A freshly bloomed bed of young flowers. "The newly budded flowers guide me on my journey, in order to reach the distance, in order to reach your side."

name: Garden Tea Party - Mature Flowers
description: A fully bloomed bed of vivid flowers. "That which greets us here is the world's warmest spring. Just listen, it's the voice of the flowers!"

name: Garden Tea Party - Hanging Flowers
description: Decorative flowers hanging in the air. "Lightly sketched ripples, lightly the flower petals wither; swayingly sketched an arc, swayingly the butterflies begin to dance."

name: Garden Tea Party - Garden Sofa
description: A sofa for tea parties. "Bear! Where? Here! I found it! Snowy white and soft! White mocha, nice and warm, let's chat together with this warm feeling!"

name: Garden Tea Party - Dusk Wilderness
description: A vista of a plain at dusk. "Running on the road that only appears once a year, basking in the dusk like an adult. Those of us that live in an hourglass, what are we? We can only use what little time we have left to find out."

name: Garden Tea Party - Thicket
description: A huge decorative thicket. "Light spills down between the trees as the flashing drops of water sing. What my eyes see in my deep sleep is a dream that you once had."

name: Garden Tea Party - Garden Fountain
description: A classic rock fountain. "I cannot become an angel. I can only become a flower by the water, so that I may soothe your heart."

name: Garden Tea Party - Flamingo
description: The lost creature, the flamingo...decoration. "Even if we can't fly in the sky, we must have the wings of dreams. That's why you must let your sweat flow. Grow up quickly and we'll conquer the skies someday!"

name: King's Tailor - "Ancient Style" Floor
description: Always remember the classical and traditional things so that you may destroy them at any time with precision.

name: King's Tailor - "Repeated Usage" Carpet
description: Would you throw away a carpet just because of a wine stain? If so, scars would all be the same as failures.

name: King's Tailor - "Starting Plan" Cabinet
description: In order to reach one's goals, it is important to carry out many plans. But what's more important is to discard even more plans.

name: King's Tailor - "Think Twice" Cupboard
description: When you have not obtained power yet, you must be careful in speech and action. When you do have power, you must be even more careful.

name: King's Tailor - "Don't Play With Fire" Sewing Table
description: Always know what your bottom line is. If you don't know, find out.

name: King's Tailor - "Self Examination" Standing Mirror
description: Remember yourself at this moment. Ensure that you are still like this when the mission has ended.

name: King's Tailor - "Exemplary Style" Wardrobe
description: An adequate supply of clothing means that you can still make it to your appointment on time after a mission. Time is forever more precious than money.

name: King's Tailor - "Alternative Compromise" Wardrobe
description: When negotiations come to a standstill, you should pick your conditions from the most to the least important --  "Compromise is within everyone's view...and this is my compromise."

name: King's Tailor - "Superficial Effort" Round Table
description: Dressing up and proper etiquettes are a kind of self-restraint. You need to distance yourself from those wild beasts through enjoying afternoon tea.

name: King's Tailor - "Necessary Virtues" Long Table
description: You can never be fully prepared, but that is exactly why you can never give up. -- "This world itself is imperfect. That's what makes it so beautiful."

name: King's Tailor - "Widely Known" Chair
description: You may be alone without support in an inferior position, but that just means that your counterattack will be all the more resplendent. -- "Witness for the last time this sacred heart, for everyone knows that it shall bloom."

name: King's Tailor - "Meeting Etiquette" Sofa
description: Being able to survive the awkward silence before the protagonist arrives is a basic skill of an underground tycoon.

name: King's Tailor - "Before the Case" Wallpaper
description: Don't let go of any clue, no matter how tiny. -- "Any intelligent being can make mistakes. Wolves can; humans can; nobody can avoid making mistakes."

name: King's Tailor - "Long-Term Target" Wall Decorations
description: The target for the future should always come from your past, not from a spur-of-the-moment decision.

name: King's Tailor - "Please Don't Knock" Shop Window
description: Perhaps this door will invite you, or perhaps you need to break and enter through the window. Opportunities are always present, but they're just not easy to notice.

name: King's Tailor - "Blow Confusion Away" Fan
description: Don't be so eager to chase away your confusion. Instead, enjoy it, until you actually get tired of it.

name: Top Jet - Display Area Floor
description: We try so hard to escape the clutches of the Earth, then struggle fervently to return to its embrace. This is the spirit of science fiction.

name: Top Jet - Mini Aircraft Runway
description: We can't put a real aircraft on it, but we can still race with RC cars on it.

name: Top Jet - V2 Missile Display
description: "The paint makes it look like a killer whale. Cruel, efficient, and cute." -- P08

name: Top Jet - "TAURUS" Missile Display
description: "Perhaps this empty shell can be converted into a canoe?" -- Gr MG5

name: Top Jet - Modern Airplane Model
description: It possesses great mobility and stability, but let's not talk about that. Do you prefer single tail or twin tail planes?

name: Top Jet - Classic Airplane Model
description: Who doesn't like that bygone era filled with unique and distinct designs? People nowadays are cleverer, but less romantic.

name: Top Jet - Ancient Aircraft Model
description: We sacrificed so much to fulfill our dreams of soaring through the sky, yet we may end up sacrificing even more after achieving it.

name: Top Jet - Civilian Rotorcraft Model
description: From a technical standpoint, the dream of flight is easily achievable, but the key to conquering the skies is possessing bravery.

name: Top Jet - Reserved Display
description: What will be the next generation of weapons? Let it be known right now that we won't launch T-Dolls as missiles.

name: Top Jet - "Styx" Missile Display
description: "It looks like a big fish. Can I keep it?!" -- MP446

name: Top Jet - "Pechora" Missile Display
description: "It sort of resembles one of those large signing pens that certain important military T-Dolls use." -- Makarov

name: Top Jet - "Tomahawk" Missile Display
description: "Looks as if you could fit someone inside... Ah, it's not like I said that they would fit in it completely." -- Ingram

name: Top Jet - Display Area Bench
description: Take a rest before you continue onwards. If your steps aren't too fast, then perhaps the clear blue sky can still catch up to us.

name: Top Jet - Display Area Wall Rack
description: Please do not climb. No matter how high you climb, you're still a long distance away from the sky.

name: Top Jet - Display Area Lighting
description: Be careful of getting burned. We can only rely on the light. We're unable to possess it, or become it.

name: Payday - Bank Secret Chamber Floor
description: The bank floor must be spotless at all times. Our staff will clean up anything on the floor ASAP, whether it be coins, bullets, or formerly living things.

name: Payday - Anti-theft Trap
description: Its ineffectiveness against most T-Dolls led some humans to believe that T-Dolls are failed imitations. They're not attracted to the most wonderful invention of human civilization, yet they are to ice cream.

name: Payday - Warehouse Hooks
description: Used for moving expensive goods or as a swing for the T-Dolls. What is the true meaning of intelligence? What's the difference between humans, T-Dolls, and apes?

name: Payday - Bank Service Desk
description: For inquiries regarding your investments, please speak with the service T-Dolls. For inquiries regarding the bank's safety, please look at the spoils of war on the counter.

name: Payday - Bank Banner
description: This banner reveals to all customers the origins of the T-Doll employees here. They can provide friendly service and stop crime at no extra cost!

name: Payday - Insurance Cargo Boxes
description: You can place your precious items inside and we'll protect it for you. Except for your heart. It's not precious anymore once you've given it away.

name: Payday - A Large Pile of World Currency
description: Gold is gold. It can buy anything in the world except for happiness, because you've already achieved happiness the moment you possess the gold.

name: Payday - A Small Pile of World Currency
description: Many T-Dolls do not understand the value of gold, so they throw the gold bars around like rocks. Or perhaps they do understand the value that the humans speak of, but they just don't understand humans.

name: Payday - Decorative Plant
description: Humans like to place these plants around various places to prove that they've once coexisted with nature, but they would then proceed to destroy it and establish a new system. And thus, the cycle repeats itself.

name: Payday - Internal Bank Notes
description: Bank notes that are only circulated between G&K T-Dolls. The exchange rate between each team is pretty big. You might wake up on a bed of it every day and exchange a stack of it just for a few lollipops.

name: Payday - Bank Forklift
description: Used for moving goods within the bank. Even though it can run automatically, some T-Dolls like to drive it themselves... Should an accident occur, a long period of deflation will follow.

name: Payday - Anti-theft Wall
description: We won't run electricity across it. How could we do such a thing! After all, wouldn't that be too kind to intruders?

name: Payday - Bank Vault
description: We need to take stock of the damages, mainly the lighting. Many of them don't light up anymore... Money? What money? It's all been spent long ago. This place is used to store chocolate coins now.

name: Payday - Flying Car Wall Decoration
description: This is just a decoration. Real cars can't break in... Other than that time on Christmas Eve with AK47 and her friends. Who knows how much they drank that night.

name: Payday - Bank Surveillance Cam
description: It knows everything that others are doing, but the only thing that it doesn't know is what itself is doing. This is the life of a camera; only wrongdoers care about it, and only remembered when something bad happens.

name: Christmas Cottage - Cozily Warm Floor
description: Careful! Overly soft T-Dolls may melt on top of it!

name: Christmas Cottage - "Winter Banquet" Carpet
description: Naive T-Dolls will like its design, serious T-Dolls will like its craftsmanship, and RFB will like the game screen presented through a pixel grid.

name: Christmas Cottage - Winter Cellar
description: Never let SPAS-12 overhear that we still have enough food. Don't you know that a shark ate everything in the warehouse last year? Yes, legends should only be half-believed, as she had only eaten half of the food in the warehouse...

name: Christmas Cottage - Tribal-Style Fireplace
description: In front of the fireplace is a long story and attentive children. It would be much easier on Mother Earth if human beings only passed down culture verbally.

name: Christmas Cottage - "Winter Training" Sandbox
description: Work makes holidays seem all the more precious and brilliant to us, just like how laymen praise suffering and the living eulogize death.

name: Christmas Cottage - "Winter Celebration" Giftboxes
description: One of the greatest pleasures of being a commander is admiring the empty expressions of T-Dolls after they excitedly open their empty giftboxes... Do apply for medical leave beforehand.

name: Christmas Cottage - Winter Food Table
description: Watch your diet? If you're not able to fully enjoy the pleasures of the hour, how will you even have the foresight to attain happiness in the future?

name: Christmas Cottage - Tribal-Style Sofa
description: Using traditional crafts as an example, many things are only missed after being forgotten, because only when it is forgotten does it seem rare and valuable.

name: Christmas Cottage - Lazy Cushion
description: You won't be able to get up once you're in its grasp. "Laziness" is the fifth force that surpasses gravity!

name: Christmas Cottage - Tribal-Style Wallpaper
description: Good things often get killed in the past, and the remains of such practices continue on even today. Even now, people flock towards it and declare it to be immortal.

name: Christmas Cottage - Tribal-Style Sculpture
description: Humanity's ancestors liked to imitate whatever they saw with their own eyes, whereas humans in the future may prefer to draw imaginary things instead.

name: Christmas Cottage - "Winter Wishes" Window
description: Even if your wish cannot be fulfilled, at the very least tell yourself that there is hope in living. When all is lost in despair, try and recall this day when you wished for happiness.

name: Pirate's Legacy - Wet Deck
description: It's forbidden to fight, litter, and roller skate on the deck. Rescuing overboard T-Dolls is very strenuous!

name: Pirate's Legacy - Window of Wind and Sunlight
description: If you think about it, the ocean is only a slightly bigger fish tank. It's just that the place you're trapped in is a bit cramped.

name: Pirate's Legacy - Lying on the Treasure
description: This is treasure that you can only obtain by betraying your own heart. Can you really sleep soundly on it? ...Of course it's more comfortable if you're heartless!

name: Pirate's Legacy - Incomplete Sea Chart
description: Humans don't want to be restricted by boundaries, yet they seek out the boundaries all the time. What lies beyond their hope must be disappointment, yet everyone flocks to it anyway.

name: Pirate's Legacy - Firepower of Justice
description: The justice of the ocean is to survive. We can talk about everything else after we get back on land.

name: Pirate's Legacy - Problem-Solving Stockpile
description: The answer to all questions can be found here, where friends and foe mingle together.

name: Pirate's Legacy - Oceanic Fast Food Restaurant
description: If anyone suddenly says that the food is delicious, please watch out for any strange behavior or actions.

name: Pirate's Legacy - Cage of Mutiny
description: Reflect well on your past actions... Stop swinging around and doing the circle dance inside!

name: Pirate's Legacy - Table of Fate
description: Feel free to pledge all your worldly possessions on the table, because no one can ensure that you won't spend it all tomorrow. Fate is such a fickle thing.

name: Pirate's Legacy - Deep Sea Lurker
description: Don't listen to what it's saying and please release it back into the ocean. I repeat, don't listen to what it's saying, and it's not tasty either. Please release it back into the ocean.

name: Pirate's Legacy - Chatty Stool - Left
description: No one cares about your story; everyone's just bored. If we don't bullshit with each other, then we can only resort to hurting each other.

name: Pirate's Legacy - Chatty Stool - Right
description: No one cares about your story; everyone's just bored. If we don't bullshit with each other, then we can only resort to hurting each other.

name: Pirate's Legacy - Haven Within the Ocean
description: Just think about it. If you're really looking for a haven on the sea, why don't you just go home?

name: Pirate's Legacy - Swaying Homeland
description: This is your heart, swaying uncertainly between the hopes of the future and the abandoned happiness of the past.

name: Pirate's Legacy - Overlooking Drapery
description: Sunshine, land, and wandering seabirds. Those things that have nothing to do with us always tend to look so much better.

name: Pixel Forest - Grassy Lawn for Adventuring
description: Spread it out on the ground, then you can tie on a bandana with a round gemstone, wear triangular shoulder pads, and embark on a wonderful journey with a gentle symphony in your ear.

name: Pixel Forest - Mysterious Fragile Brick
description: Have you ever considered that a brick could be more valuable than a copper coin?

name: Pixel Forest - Living Hammock
description: This hammock will secretly grow while you're asleep, till it's able to eat you, then...it'll start to think about life.

name: Pixel Forest - Alloy Cooking Pot
description: Make it hotter! Maybe then you can drive it!

name: Pixel Forest - Old Tank
description: It'll make your battles easier and more spectacular. In the past, you needed to win it through skills rather than with money.

name: Pixel Forest - Pensive Tree Stump
description: Tree stumps can't think about anything, but you who sits upon it can. This is very fair; you're enjoying its hospitality while it's laughing at you.

name: Pixel Forest - Brawny Sign
description: Have you ever thought about the feasibility of these oddly-shaped bullets in real life? No? Well, you can try it now.

name: Pixel Forest - Swaying Tent
description: Rest for a little while longer and immerse yourself just a little more. In the past, people fantasized in order to accept reality, whereas people now fantasize in order to escape it, or change it.

name: Pixel Forest - Passerby Bear
description: this bear won't hurt people in this world, but you can hurt it... Why don't we do so then? After all, we're the noble humans who can do whatever we want through our free will!

name: Pixel Forest - Forest of the Brave
description: Explore this expansive forest until you've eaten all the mushrooms, but the game still doesn't end.

name: Pixel Forest - Floating Treehouse
description: Building such a treehouse not only requires gathering lots of materials, you also need to determine whether your map ceiling is high enough.

name: Pixel Forest - Unwakeable Wine Bottle
description: Pick up the wine bottle and turn your life upside down. Life itself is a boring thing as there's nothing really worth enjoying besides stories.

name: Biker's Diary - Cement Floor
description: Just like a professional garage, a floor resistant to dirt and wear is always the best friend of wheels. Feel free to trample upon it if you come across it.

name: Biker's Diary - Weapons Cabinet
description: Wielding a gun on a speeding vehicle is a T-Doll's dream! Purchase this attachment now and get free lessons on fancy single-handed reloading!

name: Biker's Diary - Front Desk Tool Cabinet
description: All the most-wanted necessities for maintenance can be found here, including engine oil, anti-freeze, and of course everyone's favorite friend, WD40!

name: Biker's Diary - Merchandise Cabinet
description: Models, souvenirs, armbands, or bullets, all of these things can awaken one's hidden desire to become a biker...especially once you realize that you can't afford any of those bikes.

name: Biker's Diary - Parts Showcase
description: Customized and modified parts tend to give the user an impression of free choice. In truth, everything has already been determined, just like life itself.

name: Biker's Diary - Handle Rack
description: Compared to the actual handle itself, maybe it's more important that the handle is firmly attached to the bike...especially considering the amount of g force the Commander will endure when riding with a T-Doll.

name: Biker's Diary - Tactical Bike
description: Able to carry a large amount of military tools and even runs on petrol. You can ride it to faraway places, camps, picnics, or to stargaze... Besides escaping doomsday, you can use it to travel to any place.

name: Biker's Diary - Bike Display Rack
description: Specially placed at a prominent location in the store to show the owner's absolute confidence in these bikes, whether it is its craftsmanship, design or added value... So don't get tricked! Just buy the model that you actually need!

name: Biker's Diary - Stairway
description: Standing at a high area and overlooking motorbikes of all shapes and sizes feels just like being at a museum, but the difference being that you can personally ride one home yourself!

name: Biker's Diary - Tough Sofa
description: This series of sofas with hard textures was specially made for hardcore female T-Dolls. It takes pride in never having been stained by the slightest bit of chocolate or ice cream.

name: Biker's Diary - Military Motorbike
description: Why don't you take it? This war horse longs to return to galloping on the real battlefields instead of living within the fake scenery of war movies!

name: Biker's Diary - Warehouse Window
description: It's publicly claimed to be a warehouse storing second-hand bikes, but in truth it's specially used for storing the boss' personal bike collection. Even so, the sales staff always secretly take them out for a joyride.

name: Biker's Diary - Dismantled Parts Display Wall
description: A display wall specially designed to create an extraordinary atmosphere within the shop. Children like to stand in front of it and stare. The display items are usually placed high up to avoid letting these fearsome creatures from leaving fingerprints.

name: Biker's Diary - Bikes to be Sold
description: If they're left unsold for a long time, the technicians in the maintenance department will usually dismantle them to use as parts for fixing other bikes. Many stories are left behind, though no one's ever heard of them, but there have been people who've experienced it themselves.

name: Hometown Reminiscence - Little Artists in the Snow
description: Chicks draw bamboo leaves, puppies draw plum blossoms, ducklings draw maple leaves, foals draw cresent moons... What're the children running over here for? They've messed up the drawings!

name: Hometown Reminiscence - Popcorn Machine
description:
This is a traditional popcorn baking tool from China. Though it looks more like an apparatus for evil alchemists, I assure you that it is very saf-- BOOM!
This the reason why everyone thought Type56R just returned from the coal mines.

name: Hometown Reminiscence - Auspicious Start
description: It is used to chase away unluckiness and thieving birds, but it doesn't work on little children. In fact, it has the opposite effect on them. They'll take away your gong and mallet...and then your sleep.

name: Hometown Reminiscence - Plum Blossoms by the Corner
description:
Can't you learn anything from the resilient plum blossoms? -- Type88 
People who're willing to suffer won't have friends. -- Type80

name: Hometown Reminiscence - Firecracker Store
description:
Unlike gunfire, fireworks usually represent joy and happiness... -- Type95
But isn't obtaining victory through gunfire joyous as well? What's the difference! -- Type97

name: Hometown Reminiscence - Small Ice-Lantern
description:
Help! The T-Dolls of Griffin have cast a spell of ice on me! Only the kiss of true love can... -- ??
Can make you edible? Then I'm gonna kiss you! -- Type56-1
No, please, stop! I'm coming out right now! -- T65

name: Hometown Reminiscence - Weathered Frozen Branches
description:
What did you want to teach me? -- Type63 
Inviting a friend here to kick at a tree is a common folk entertainment...and sport! Hahahaha, come and catch me! -- Type59

name: Hometown Reminiscence - Snack Shop
description:
Don't throw away the bamboo skewers after you finish eating. We can keep on using them for the next year. -- Type92 
We've already used them for two years! Even sustainable living should have a limit! -- Type79 
If there's a limit, then why would it be called sustainable living? -- Type92

name: Hometown Reminiscence - Snowkid
description: The secret to a snowman's growth is longer periods of cruel weather and not having anyone to play with... What a weird fellow.

name: Hometown Reminiscence - Small Tea Table
description:
I heard that you guys chat while drinking tea. Aren't you afraid of choking? -- T91 
The topic we're discussing right now is whether or not you guys will choke. -- Type64

name: Hometown Reminiscence - Symphony of Frost and Flame
description: To young humans, there's no difference between firecrackers and gunfire. Both are used for entertainment, are lethal, and are only used at places inconvenient to clean up.

name: Hometown Reminiscence - Small Bamboo Stool - Right
description: The creaky noise and the strict requirements on the sitting posture makes some neurotic science students very uncomfortable. Perhaps this is why ancient China was not very advanced in science.

name: Hometown Reminiscence - Small Bamboo Stool - Left
description: The creaky noise and the strict requirements on the sitting posture makes some neurotic science students very uncomfortable. Perhaps this is why ancient China was not very advanced in science.

name: Hometown Reminiscence - Campstool
description:
An important tool in day-to-day life. It is used during gossiping, visiting friends and family, sitting in vehicles, and even when fighting with others. -- Type97S
Please, don't give me any more trouble! -- Type81R

name: Hometown Reminiscence - Blessings at the Gate
description:
New year, new scene! -- JS05
You're the only new one here. Is it really necessary to celebrate? -- NZ75
We should celebrate the fact that everyone is here! -- JS05

name: Echelon Collection - Tactical Floor
description: It seemingly gives off a hard-boiled commander vibe. Of course, most of the differences between a hard-boiled and a regular commander can be summed up as only "seemingly".

name: Echelon Collection - Tactical Doll AK-12
description: A life sized figure based on a T-Doll who always keeps her eyes closed. She is curious about everything, but rarely does she get involved. She's well aware that having a wild nature is an unstable bomb.

name: Echelon Collection - Tactical Cutout CZ75
description: A cutout of a violent T-Doll who is not good at expressing herself. She likes to solve issues and goodwill shown to her with actions rather than words... Yes, "solve"...

name: Echelon Collection - Tactical Cutout S.A.T.8
description: A cutout of a cheerful and stable T-Doll. She tends to lose her mind in unexpected situations and when she encounters cute things. Forget it, I take my words back. She's not so stable after all.

name: Echelon Collection - Tactical Cutout M99
description: A cutout of a well-behaved and gentle T-Doll. She likes rabbits and cooking, but don't you dare cook rabbits in front of her, or she'll bite you.

name: Echelon Collection - Leisure Manga Shelf
description: Please observe the golden rule before you start flipping through a manga; make sure that the final chapter is on the shelf.

name: Echelon Collection - Leisure Anime Figure Shelf
description: "Money CAN buy happiness!" A sincere thought of yours as you stand before your shelf full of anime figures. In other words, "I just want everyone to be happy!"

name: Echelon Collection - Leisure Equipment Shelf
description: It is used to store what was the latest tech gadgets on the market. Also known as the irrational consumer museum...or the dust collector.

name: Echelon Collection - Leisure Coffee Table
description: Cozy moments are always invaluable. You need to work hard for a day like today. Perhaps you should just do nothing and enjoy the moment.

name: Echelon Collection - Leisure Games Shelf
description: You say the games of today are nowhere as fun as the games of the past. You say the games have changed, you have changed, and the times have changed. In fact, nothing has changed as long as you still enjoy them.

name: Echelon Collection - Leisure Game Console
description:
《What is the future》
"Wanna guess what the games will be like in the future? Maybe we'll have multiplayer Pong in color with score tracking!"
"Welcome to the future-"
"My god..."

name: Echelon Collection - Tactical Computer Chair
description: An office chair with a futuristic feel to it. Futuristic meaning laziness, and laziness meaning a better life.

name: Echelon Collection - Leisure Computer Chair - Left
description: This chair is not leisurely at all, especially when you want to take a nap or put your arms on the armrests pretending to contemplate. This is an unfortunate product from humanity's course of scientific exploration.

name: Echelon Collection - Leisure Computer Chair - Right
description: This chair is not leisurely at all, especially when you want to take a nap or put your arms on the armrests pretending to contemplate. This is an unfortunate product from humanity's course of scientific exploration.

name: Echelon Collection - Leisure Lazy Chair - Red
description: The world is dying, but we don't care as we melt away on this chair.

name: Echelon Collection - Leisure Lazy Chair - Blue
description: Don't worry so much, wasting time is mankind's specialty. Best not to ruin it.

name: Echelon Collection - Tactical Steel Wall
description: It has fantastic sound insulation. You can easily do something you enjoy in secrecy, like working overtime.

name: Echelon Collection - Tactical Lights
description: It comes with a [open reference mode] tactical [end reference mode] mode. Prior to each and every use, please scan your iris at the terminal and provide the nail color of the current T-Doll on duty as the secret answer.

name: Wedding Scenery - Wedding Grass Field
description: The grass represents natural purity, although we had to burn the weeds and trim the grass. The same goes for the ceremony.

name: Wedding Scenery - Photographic Dolly Track
description: To film a beautiful long take for a movie or a video game, we need good cinematography and T-Doll actresses willing to follow the script.

name: Wedding Scenery - Castle Wall - Far
description: Background of a castle wall that stands far off into the distance. Or maybe it's just small rather than far.

name: Wedding Scenery - Castle Wall - Near
description: Background of a castle wall that stands nearby. It's very big, so you best hope that you're standing between the arches if it collapses on you.

name: Wedding Scenery - Castle Gate - Background
description: Background of a castle gate that stands in the center. Ignore that thing dangling at the top and pretend everything is real. Just like your feelings.

name: Wedding Scenery - Photography Director's Seat
description: Sit in the seat and pretend to be in control of everything. Even if things had already been decided in advance, you still have the chance to mess things up.

name: Wedding Scenery - Wedding Convertible Car
description: How can you tell it's not tears of joy if someone is crying in this car?

name: Wedding Scenery - Photographic Film Light
description: Like darkness, light can also obscure the truth. That's right, the purpose of art is to obscure the truth in the first place.

name: Wedding Scenery - Photography Camera
description: It has the great honor of witnessing human history, but don't ask it whether nuclear bomb or chocolate is the greater invention.

name: Wedding Scenery - Wedding Arbor
description: I'm really envious of this thing. It only ever bears witness to the moment of happiness, and not the bumpy roads prior to and after this moment.

name: Wedding Scenery - Cinema Camera
description: It knows the world is alive, much more than we do, because it doesn't need to think about extraneous things.

name: Wedding Scenery - Photographic Background Wall
description: Its existence suggests that everything here is for the sake of an image. Anything you can touch is never that romantic.

name: Wedding Scenery - Photographic Sky Screen
description: Is the real life behind the screen, or is it an impassable wall? Is there even a difference?

name: Wedding Scenery - Photographic Softbox
description: It makes pictures more beautiful than the truth... Who likes the truth anyway? The truth is basically a troop of lying monkeys.

name: Wedding Scenery - Wedding Table
description: What else is there to do besides leaving after eating at the wedding party? Happiness is short-lived, so enjoy it to your heart's content before you'll have to look back on it.

name: Wedding Scenery - Wedding Chairs
description: It matters not who, but how many sit on these seats. The sole purpose of the people on these seats in the movies is to form a rowdy crowd for the bouquet toss scene anyway.

name: Swimming Fish, Flying Geese - Long Stone Path
description: Do you only feel grounded when you step on it? But it's so uneven...

name: Swimming Fish, Flying Geese - Lush Grass and Fluffy Clouds
description: Some of the little buds have already blossomed, and they might be very happy to know that you noticed.

name: Swimming Fish, Flying Geese - Little Bridge Crossing
description: Do you know how happy the fish are? The fish don't know how happy you are, and they don't want to know.

name: Swimming Fish, Flying Geese - Long-Lasting Lamp
description: You need to stand on a bench to top up its oil, which was why mankind invented the electric light.

name: Swimming Fish, Flying Geese - Ancestral Altar
description: The thoughts you let wander can't go anywhere, and in the end they will flow back to your heart. But hopefully their journey will give you strength.

name: Swimming Fish, Flying Geese - Tri-colored Gong
description: The three colors represent Heaven, Earth and Man coming together, but from scientific and life experiences, the three of them won't mix.

name: Swimming Fish, Flying Geese - Foothill General
description: You put it here to bring you fortune, but all it thinks about is who will turn off the tap and leaving this hollow modern world behind.

name: Swimming Fish, Flying Geese - Eucalyptus Stone Lantern
description: It's warm in front of the lamp and cool under the trees. The person sitting between them is bored, what a shame that it isn't me.

name: Swimming Fish, Flying Geese - Forest Brook
description: It was initially made to scare the birds away, but in this age the birds won't come even if you bribe them with breadcrumbs.

name: Swimming Fish, Flying Geese - Cooling Backyard
description: Yes, you need a big house if you roll around in your sleep. Perhaps money was made for people with various deficiencies.

name: Swimming Fish, Flying Geese - Cat-Finding Diary
description: The cats love you, but they still get lost. You should love yourself, even if you lose yourself from time to time.

name: Swimming Fish, Flying Geese - Front Yard Tree
description: Only the bedding and the pillow are necessary, as everything else is just a lifestyle decoration, be it the walls, the tree, or valuable pottery.

name: Swimming Fish, Flying Geese - Springtime Nap in the Grass
description: People are sleepy in spring, sleepless in summer, snoring in autumn, and unwakeable in winter. Happiness is not worrying about whether the time you've spent has been wasted.

name: Convention Craze - Convention Floor
description: No shoes? No problem. Just step on all the long skirts that drag on the floor.

name: Convention Craze - Autograph Table
description: Please refrain from photographing or video-recording. All that exists here is a human being quietly signing autographs with a big heart of love.

name: Convention Craze - Convention Promo Ad
description: The promo ad is an important aspect of convention-goer attraction, so let's get started! Now is the time to compete with the other booths on who has the louder speakers!

name: Convention Craze - Convention Lights
description: These lights are never too dazzling not because they want to appear ordinary, but because there is always something even more striking at a convention.

name: Convention Craze - On-Site Factory Display
description: Is luck also an aspect of power...? No, luck is everything when it comes to power.

name: Convention Craze - Merchandise Crowd
description: Take advantage of your time in the queue to sensibly reorganize your shopping bags to make a contribution to the orderly conduct of the convention and the harmonious law and unity of the universe.

name: Convention Craze - Autograph Crowd
description: What is this line for? Perhaps it's just a name, or perhaps it's an embodiment of deep respect engraved onto paper.

name: Convention Craze - Convention Crowd Barrier
description: A convention is like a besieged city. The people outside want in, and the people inside want out.

name: Convention Craze - On-Site Command Display
description: Give your order, Commander! By the way, stand here to put yourself into the shoes of an adjutant to experience her job and understand her feelings.

name: Convention Craze - Merchandise Showcase
description: One does not need too many Dinergates in life, and in fact, what DO you need besides the basic life necessities? Perhaps a Dinergate can show you.

name: Convention Craze - On-Site Cutout
description: Life-sized cutout of a Tactical Doll. Sometimes the actual T-Doll in question or her sister will personally retrieve this cutout after the end of a convention.

name: Convention Craze - On-Site Photographer
description: If the lens focal length is really that important then why do we still need image editing software?

name: Convention Craze - On-Site Ad Board
description:
Everyone can clearly see this T-Doll is nothing more than a huge decoration...
Until she suddenly moves and shouts "I AM HUNGRY!"

name: Convention Craze - Merchandise Table
description: "Welcome, Commander! You're finally here after lining up for so long in this sea of people! So...since you're here, why don't you buy something?" -- Kalina

name: Convention Craze - Merchandise Rack
description: The majority of these T-Dolls probably don't wish to stay on this rack forever! Please rescue them now!

name: Convention Craze - On-Site Command Chair
description: Anything that has to do with war is decorated in an extravagant manner. That's why the chair in Griffin Control is much more luxurious than this one.

name: Convention Craze - Convention Venue
description: No gods or kings, only man. That's right, there are only humans here! They're all humans!

name: Saturday Night Fever - Dance Club Flooring
description: Smooth and glossy enough to put the flooring outside to shame, this flooring will gradually lose its dignity with each and every spilled drink and dropped snack.

name: Saturday Night Fever - Dance Pad
description: This kind of plebeian entertainment equipment is built upon sophisticated mathematics and artistic designs, so wake up, people! Everything is under the control of the ruling elite!

name: Saturday Night Fever - Revelrous Drinks Table
description: Let's place snacks and drinks on this table and flip everything over all at once! Why shouldn't I? The life we bear is heavier than the table we fling once a year!

name: Saturday Night Fever - Party Mini Fridge
description: To tonight, cheers! ...But don't throw the bottles away, because Type92 will take and sell them.

name: Saturday Night Fever - Anniversary Cake
description: Savor it to your heart's content for all the free souls out there! Just note that every bite adds to your gravitational field!

name: Saturday Night Fever - Party Floor Lamp
description: The light of this lamp serves as a corner of tranquil refuge within the party's neon haze. So what do you want to talk about? The weather? Or do you want to hear a story?

name: Saturday Night Fever - Mascot Balloons
description: Submersed in a beautiful ambience waiting for their own destiny, they will either slowly deflate within a sea of laughter or be popped underfoot by opportunistic pranksters.

name: Saturday Night Fever - Party Turntable Mixer
description: Your guests will still bob their heads to the rhythm no matter how rebellious they claim to be, just like how the motorcyclists that love to roar down the streets will still stop at a red light.

name: Saturday Night Fever - Dance Club Wallpaper
description: Everything is born from darkness, and even the lively party is but a fleeting moment in time. Once you leave, it'll be very lonely.

name: Saturday Night Fever - Night View Window
description: Are you concerned about the world outside the window? Some are starving and some are crying, so shouldn't you be happier with what you have, just like how salted fruits taste sweeter?

name: Saturday Night Fever - Old Party Posters
description: Some eras are very far gone, while some eras have only recently passed. Nevertheless, they're all times of the past. There's no present, only tomorrow.

name: Saturday Night Fever - Revelrous Neon Sign
description: Let us party tonight! Because the T-Doll depicted by this decoration will surely smash it to bits by tomorrow morning!

name: Saturday Night Fever - Star Lights
description: These are not real stars; the real stars are hidden in a faraway place. Not to mention, they may not be very welcoming of us.

name: Saturday Night Fever - Tiger Couch
description: The tiger plush doll will not eat you, but the couch might, and then it'll spit you back out in the morning.

name: Saturday Night Fever - Revelrous Sofa Chair
description: Sitting across from your sofa chair, the other person listens to you intently in the midst of the unchecked cacophony. Perhaps they like you, or perhaps they're drunk, or maybe even both. Tonight may be all the time you have.

name: Star of Amusement Park - Amusement Park Stone Floor
description: The dirty floor proves that the amusement park is popular, so is the floor happy about it? Maybe we should hire some more stupid stone bricks.

name: Star of Amusement Park - Clear Sky Castle
description: Are those who yearn for castles above love more realistic? Are those who pursue love rather than castles braver?

name: Star of Amusement Park - Popcorn Cart
description: Please don't bring it to any entertainment facilities. Who would have the heart to let one that has forged a new, independent life back into chaos?

name: Star of Amusement Park - Shooting Game
description: Every prize won is a Dinergate shot dead! ...So what are you waiting for? Restore your incomplete childhood! Human, become the bully!

name: Star of Amusement Park - Amusement Park Eggs Lights
description: It has been bound by the earth for too long. Once its popularity heats up, it will hatch birds in search of the blue sky.

name: Star of Amusement Park - Planetary Cruiser
description: You will not arrive in outer space on this ride. Especially not after you grow up.

name: Star of Amusement Park - Cyclone Roller Coaster
description: There are countless possibilities in the future of mankind, but it is impossible to replace wars with the screams on the roller coaster.

name: Star of Amusement Park - Cyclone Station Platform
description: This is your last chance to change your mind! I know that you were kidnapped here by your friends. Now is the time to fight for freedom!

name: Star of Amusement Park - Souvenir Shop
description: Is there anything more commemorative than photos and souvenirs? Don't tell me memories?

name: Star of Amusement Park - Cotton Candy Shop
description: People usually compare dreams to cotton candies. Believe me, dreams are far less soft and delicious.

name: Star of Amusement Park - Bumper Car Square
description: Want to drive a real car? Then you can't bump around like you don't care!

name: Star of Amusement Park - Amusement Park Ticket Gate
description: Come and buy some happiness! Otherwise why are you here? Is reality that terrible?

name: Star of Amusement Park - Vertical Shuttle Ride
description: People use this facility to experience death during peacetime. Maybe the false things are not necessarily wrong, whether it be their feelings or T-Dolls.

name: South Sea Pavilion - Square Stone Tiles
description: It's not flooring. The kids are uncomfortable when playing on it, and some of them even caught a cold. Thus, everyone thinks poorly of it.

name: South Sea Pavilion - Little Rainforest Park
description: Look outside and realize that you're only a short distance away from true nature. Forests that will swallow you up, the sticky air, and cruel mosquitoes all await you.

name: South Sea Pavilion - Pavilion Counter
description: It provides you with drinks and music. Only customers who buy beverages may change the music, and for a small tip you can adjust the volume too.

name: South Sea Pavilion - Patterned Carpet
description: Some people may notice the intricate and beautiful patterns. These people are often unhappy with the real world, so be careful hanging around them.

name: South Sea Pavilion - Wine Cabinet
description: The cabinet displays many famous wines and spirits, but they're packed so tightly that changing the bottles out is hard, so they're not for sale.

name: South Sea Pavilion - Potted Banana
description: The poets saw that the bananas were lonely, and so the poems they wrote for them have endured through the ages, but what exactly is loneliness? Perhaps only the bananas know, or perhaps it is only the bananas that don't know.

name: South Sea Pavilion - Potted Dandelion
description: The historians discovered to their surprise that these ornamental plants had been made into hand fans for over 1000 years. There's no need to make a fuss, though; after all, hand fans have been gone for nearly 50 years!

name: South Sea Pavilion - Pavilion Sofa
description: Hotel sofas typically only do their job when guests are about to leave, so the only thing they remember are people's backs.

name: South Sea Pavilion - Beverage Cart
description: Have a drink and forget some of your ideals. Travel can't change anyone, because people are all the same no matter which part of the world you visit.

name: South Sea Pavilion - Dessert Cart
description: Once people think of self-service without limits, they'll eat lots of food even if it tastes bad - mankind created art to fight the thing known as "desire".

name: South Sea Pavilion - Breakfast Table
description: To travel is to eat breakfast in a different seat, take calls in a different room, and consider the things that are bothering you from a different angle.

name: South Sea Pavilion - Pavilion Chair
description: In inns, chairs like these are mainly used to store luggage. After all, what most people do and what they want to do tend to have no relation to each other.

name: South Sea Pavilion - Pavilion Parrot
description: Many people can also repeat what you say unconditionally, and you don't need to feed them either. They just have to be bored enough.

name: South Sea Pavilion - Pavilion Square Table
description: Have a good discussion with your travelling companions about your upcoming plans. Then break them all, one by one, and fully enjoy the little things on your journey.

name: South Sea Pavilion - Pavilion Dining Table
description: Perhaps I ought to chat with the person sitting opposite of me. Our connection to the world shouldn't be limited to the newspaper at the breakfast table.

name: Takeoff to Happiness - Airport Flooring
description: A variety of interesting people pass by on these floor tiles, but they don't have the time to discover each other's interesting side. We always assume that interesting things are at the destination. This is the essence of travelling.

name: Takeoff to Happiness - Airport Scenery
description: Why is such a large space necessary for planes? Why not just prepare a parachute for each passenger? Some problems do not stem from curiosity, but rather the opposite of it.

name: Takeoff to Happiness - Airport Bar Counter
description: Every food and drink is expensive, and how to waste time gracefully is a luxury.

name: Takeoff to Happiness - Airport ATM
description: All financial problems can be solved here, but the idiot in front of you that can't figure out how to withdraw money can only be solved by you.

name: Takeoff to Happiness - Airport Bar Stool
description: Is the person sitting next to you an unlucky fellow with a delayed flight? Or is he a worrywart that arrived five hours in advance of his flight?

name: Takeoff to Happiness - Airport Transport
description: How nice it would be if all means of transportation are as cheap and safe as this transport vehicle. Maybe we don't need to go that fast after all?

name: Takeoff to Happiness - Flight Boarding Gate
description: Line up at the front to be the first to claim a spot for your luggage and prevent others from doing so. Cherish this opportunity. There are not many opportunities to legally hurt others.

name: Takeoff to Happiness - Airport TV
description: The show will never be the show you want to watch, but sometimes you can't help yourself.

name: Takeoff to Happiness - Airport Ad Board
description: Is your destination a journey full of expectations? A place to unwind? Or is it dull and numb work? Please don't ignore the process. I wish you a happy journey in the air!

name: Takeoff to Happiness - Airport Ad Picture
description: Come buy some souvenirs! Otherwise why would anyone feel happy about you coming here? It's not like you can gift the pictures away!

name: Takeoff to Happiness - Flight Schedule
description: Where are the destinations of these flights? What are the people on these flights for? Things that have nothing to do with us form the world.

name: Takeoff to Happiness - Airport Signpost
description: The experience of others is just like these signs. It only tells you the direction but not the distance to your destination. You're more likely to run into a toilet than where you're supposed to go.
