name: Takeoff to Happiness - Self-Service Luggage Machine
description: Dangerous goods are forbidden on planes. Anyone relieved at having brought dangerous goods onboard without being caught tends to think of themselves as much more important than others.

name: Takeoff to Happiness - Waiting Seats
description: We always think that time is still early, but it always comes faster than expected, whether it be a flight or a turning point in life.

name: Beach Tycoon - Beachy Outdoor Floorboard
description: Sunshine and sea breeze will take care of the seawater and sand on the floor, but stubs...will have to be settled by hand... I mean...stabs.

name: Beach Tycoon - The Sky and the Reef
description: The reef feels perfectly comfortable with its head against the sky and its body soaking in the sea. Have the sky and the sea been apart since the very beginning of time or only since humans started developing intelligence?

name: Beach Tycoon - Adventures of the Lightning Cat
description: At least in the short duration while you're sliding down the pipe, you can briefly enjoy a world without Miss IDW.

name: Beach Tycoon - Seagull Magic
description: Sea birds and fish never fall in love with each other. If they were that clever, they would scoff at romance among humans.

name: Beach Tycoon - Dolphin Challenge Playground
description: An entertainment facility so complex visitors often have no idea what they've just been through afterwards... That's the challenge.

name: Beach Tycoon - Deep Sea Staircase (For Children)
description: It doesn't lead to the sea, or anywhere deep. It's not even a staircase. It just sounds cool, like..."human love".

name: Beach Tycoon - Swordfish Billboard
description: Judging by observation, swordfish is probably more intelligent than humans, since a lot of visitors can't find the restaurant or the washrooms without a swordfish totem.

name: Beach Tycoon - Splashy Hovercraft
description: Like humans, they can still run around as long as there's air in them. Perhaps even a hovercraft has plans for its life.

name: Beach Tycoon - Sandy Throne
description: A person who has the prerogative to rest is more eminent whether in a palace or on a beach. This is what the chair and leadership entail.

name: Beach Tycoon - Barbecue Time
description: What feels even better than having a barbecue on the beach? ...Having a barbecue on the beach next to people who've only bought instant noodles, of course!

name: Beach Tycoon - Intercontinental Battleship (For Children)
description: You won't know how intense that battle was since hovercrafts leave no trace, just as how traces of dinosaurs can't be found on the earth's surface after they've gone extinct.

name: Beach Tycoon - Mr. Crocodile's Pool
description: Mr. Crocodile has an electric switch. He automatically flips over after someone's been lying on them for over 30 minutes. He just won't let anyone enjoy a nice nap! Bad Mr. Crocodile!

name: Music Festival - Dancefloor
description: Stars under my feet, rainbow over my head. Thousands of verses and songs, written just so my head can reconcile with my heart.

name: Music Festival - Stage Background
description: These are people who tried searching for their own sense of self but ended up becoming just another face in the crowd.

name: Music Festival - Bar Stool
description: The stool is high because the bar is high. The bar is high because the bartender can reach it. There, who do you think are the real bosses in the service industry?

name: Music Festival - Performance Stage
description: I suppose one reason why rock music is more stimulating than classical music is because the audience has to stand and look up at the stage.

name: Music Festival - Footlight
description: Footlights are even more selfless than candles. Nobody looks at them, but they still shine upon others.

name: Music Festival - Spotlight
description: Without darkness, what use is an artificial ring of light, no matter how bright?

name: Music Festival - Stage Arch
description: Step through this arch and show your best side! Or maybe your worst side... Anything that isn't your genuine self!

name: Music Festival - Fans
description: Binding your life to someone else's song is still safer than binding it to someone else's heart.

name: Music Festival - Champagne
description: Civilization is systematic squandering of resources. Well-wishes are sophisticated superstition.

name: Music Festival - Minibar
description: Your life and your story are two different things. Your pour the former into your own glass and the latter into the other person's glass.

name: Music Festival - Club Chair - Right
description: Nothing is crazier than someone sitting through a live rock concert.

name: Music Festival - Club Chair - Left
description: Nothing is crazier than someone sitting through a live rock concert.

name: Music Festival - Club Table
description: The lights illuminate the liquor while music shoves its way through us. How much do we have to hate ourselves before the world finally shows its true colors?

name: Haunted Castle - Spooky Floorboards
description: What's the matter? It's just ordinary flooring. Don't think it's anything out of the ordinary just because you found it in a haunted house - The Floor

name: Haunted Castle - Last Window
description: Once the morning comes, you can wake up and leave, but... are you awake now? ...Heehee, I'm asking you.

name: Haunted Castle - Automated Fireplace
description: The oppressed castle servants died of overwork, and the flames of their wrath now incinerate any firewood thrown into the fireplace -- which helps a lot.

name: Haunted Castle - Electrocat Lanterns
description: Supports switching between "Electrocat Lantern" and "Lantern Electrocat" -- As long as you hang it around IDW's neck!

name: Haunted Castle - Swaying Chandelier
description: This chandelier sways non-stop and can serve as both a light source and a metronome. If you need to change its speed just talk to the kid hanging around.

name: Haunted Castle - Uneasy Carpet
description: This carpet has severe claustrophobia and wants to fly outside, so you should probably weigh it down with furniture.

name: Haunted Castle - Unsleeping Coffin
description: This living coffin works when you rest and rests while you work. If you oversleep, it'll dump you out.

name: Haunted Castle - Magic Mirror of Destiny
description: This mirror is inhabited by a ghost that's paid to scare people. It hates young female tenants, because it has to do overtime.

name: Haunted Castle - Potion Cabinet
description: This cabinet is filled with various magic items and products. It gets very angry if they're not arranged by type and order.

name: Haunted Castle - Half-Body Knight
description: It walks around every night to scare people, but once we found that there was actually someone inside it wasn't scary anymore.

name: Haunted Castle - Castle Banner
description: This is the back of the banner. Its front is a miserable face. It recounts all the sins it committed in its previous life to the wall, and then continues sinning.

name: Haunted Castle - Ghostly Armchair
description: Inhabited by the vengeful spirits of those who died in the castle, they only found this comfortable sofa chair after parting, and they get very jealous when you sit on it.

name: Haunted Castle - Barren Cage
description: This cage is inhabited by the spirit of a princess -- she wanted to use it to slim down, but in the end she stuffed herself to death inside it.

name: Haunted Castle - Haunted Bench
description: A ghost died on it, and it has vowed never to leave because it feels far superior to its neighbors on the sofa.

name: Haunted Castle - Wicked Banquet
description: After the ritual, everyone gathers to partake in this revolting and heretical fare -- haha, were you scared? Fooled you! How could anyone eat their own kind?

name: Burger of Bliss - Slick Flooring
description: Ever since a dog slipped and fell in the store, the animal rights association asked us to only mop the floor once a week and spill cola on it to maintain its stickiness.

name: Burger of Bliss - "Toffee Season" Wallpaper
description: Do you feel a sense of austere, yet comfortable beauty when you gaze upon this wall? If not, it means that we've been tricked by our interior designer.

name: Burger of Bliss - "Legendary Customer" Neon Lights
description: These neon lights are used to commemorate the winner of the yearly Big Eater competition, but we haven't changed this one ever since we put it in.

name: Burger of Bliss - "Business Hours" Kitchen Window
description: We hope this helps you understand how passionate we are about our work, and how much we hate vegetarians.

name: Burger of Bliss - "Twilight Code" Hanging Lights
description: When only two lights are on, it means wandering Dolls can stay the night. When only one light is on, it means humans working the night shift can come squeeze in too.

name: Burger of Bliss - "Cool Vision" Ceiling Fan
description: You normally won't notice a ceiling fan, but you'll notice if it's gone. This effect is known as the...who cares what those damn academics call it.

name: Burger of Bliss - "Happy Adjutant" Statue
description:
I don't know what's wrong with it, but I keep thinking that a statue that's meant to make people happy shouldn't look like that... 
 "The statue isn't meant to make people happy. She's very happy to begin with. You need to think about it from her perspective." 
 "But I AM Kalina..."
 "And that's why you're a superficial being, a chaotic and easily-changed reference, while the statue has a more...stable nature."

name: Burger of Bliss - "Delicious Stage" Display Case
description: This display case is filled to the brim with mankind's history of ingesting the most amount of calories in the shortest possible time. While you don't have to be moved by it, you have to pay for it.

name: Burger of Bliss - "Happy Rainbow" Drinks
description: We change the drinks every day depending on our mood...or just their coloring.

name: Burger of Bliss - "Space Voyage" Neon Lights
description: If burgers are flying saucers and the restaurant is the universe, then what are we? We're just a bunch of unimportant nebulae, and the stomach is the end of the universe.

name: Burger of Bliss - "Devil's Lava" Statue
description: Is it a song? Is it a book? Is it a person? No! The only thing that can truly warm your heart is calories, so put on another slice of cheese!

name: Burger of Bliss - "Gold Experience" Roasting Case
description: Do you remember how many loaves of bread you've eaten in your lifetime? We'll help you, just pass us the bill.

name: Burger of Bliss - "Top Secret" Hatch
description: The secret that lays within is that only lives that are lost hold value.

name: Burger of Bliss - "Potato Crystal" Neon Light
description: The world faces a gamble - take a bet on whether nuclear weapons or junk food will destroy our bodies first.

name: Burger of Bliss - "Noisy Afternoon" Dining Table
description: Spend a mindless and enjoyable weekend amidst the laughter of your best friends! Put all your worries out of sight and out of mind, after all, you've already paid up.

name: Burger of Bliss - "Soul Sacrifice" Dining Seat
description: Relax and eat! Food won't change you, it only changes how other people look at you, and it's not like you can change that, right?

name: Burger of Bliss - "Centimeter Guess" Dining Seat
description: Do you like beer and fried chicken, or some cola with a burger? Do you like the view from the window in the morning, or the corner in the evening? I remembered the answers, but forgot the questions, because I don't know where you are.

name: Burger of Bliss - "Waiting Alone" Dining Seat
description: There are some things you have to desperately chase after, and other things you have to be content to wait for. Some of these things could hold joy, bliss, fried chicken, or perhaps even you.

name: Operation Idol - Dance Floor
description: The person standing on the C positions is determined by 10% fan votes, 20% tragic pasts, 30% today's MVP and 99% affection for the Commander.

name: Operation Idol - Shiny Skyline
description: Tonight, there's no way the city can outshine the stage...or be more disruptive.

name: Operation Idol - Supportive Audience
description: Everyone, raise your hands higher! Try and cover your faces!

name: Operation Idol - Moonlight Avenue
description: The glass under the idols' feet is rigged; step on the wrong tile and you'll be fed to the fishes.

name: Operation Idol - Rainbow Stairs
description: The lights inside can change rapidly as the idols enter and exit the stage; the Dolls use them to test their neural reaction speeds when they're bored. "A Doll that's faster than light!"

name: Operation Idol - Stage Doll
description: Made with a leftover Dummy neural cloud, they have the IQ of a 5 year old and can accept and play simple messages, such as "please take my songs home."

name: Operation Idol - Close-Up Screen
description: If we entrust our souls to idols, does that mean their images on the screen better reflect what's in our hearts?

name: Operation Idol - Tracked Boom
description: It allows idols to perform mid-air spins and other marvellous stunts, whether they want to or not.

name: Operation Idol - Stage Catwalk
description: Typically used during the second chorus, the stage entrance methods it supports include (but are not limited to) orbital launches, HALO dives and floor slides.

name: Operation Idol - Judges' Seat
description: There are no good or bad singing voices, just as there are no right or wrong dreams, although the sound technicians and backup band might not think so.

name: Operation Idol - Theme Screen
description: The center screen isn't solid, so the idols can go straight through it as they move around the stage, or even make a secret exit in the middle of a dance number.

name: Operation Idol - Stage Camera
description: The idols all want their best moments to be recorded, but their screw-ups are usually more widely known.

name: Operation Idol - Teleprompter
description: It has a wireless transmitter inside; when a Doll can't find the right lyrics or tunes, it instantly transmits a segment of backup data into their neural cloud.

name: Operation Idol - Lighting Scaffold
description: It makes the idols shine and doubles as a module charger. "Awaken, Returner!"

name: Operation Idol - Stage Speakers
description: The point of attending a live concert is that you'll never know if the person singing on the other side of the screen is a Doll or a puppet.

name: Night at the Candy Museum - Biscuit Flooring
description: If you bite a big hole into it, you'll lose your footing and fall from your dreams into reality, so make sure you save it for last.

name: Night at the Candy Museum - Candy Wrapper Canopy
description: Filling the world with happiness is tiresome, so the lazy Creator invented "dreams", leaving the task of "happiness" to ourselves.

name: Night at the Candy Museum - Dessert Conveyor Belt
description: All snacks go out to the world from here. Don't worry, they'll sleep soundly on their long journey and get eaten without suffering.

name: Night at the Candy Museum - White Chocolate Chandelier - Left
description: Every white chocolate candle is a sleeping sun. Once they burn out, you'll wake up amidst the morning light.

name: Night at the Candy Museum - White Chocolate Chandelier - Right
description: Every white chocolate candle is a sleeping sun. Once they burn out, you'll wake up amidst the morning light.

name: Night at the Candy Museum - Cookie Counter
description: How many biscuit and snack tins are grateful to be born? If you could plan out your life before you began it, what would it be like?

name: Night at the Candy Museum - Present Shelf
description: If the shelf doesn't have what you want, try looking deeper inside... When you have no idea what you want, "no idea" is what you want.

name: Night at the Candy Museum - Peace Accords
description: The generals of the Candy Jar Kingdom and the Dessert Bucket Nation are now signing a new peace treaty. Hopefully this truce will last until the Christmas Eve banquet.

name: Night at the Candy Museum - Nice Kids List
description: Who are the good children who'll get presents this Christmas? Don't feel down if you don't get one, kids, I'm sure that next year, you'll...have gotten used to it!

name: Night at the Candy Museum - Candy Christmas Tree
description: Don't be tempted by the sweets and focus on climbing upwards, dear children; when you grow up, you won't be able to live for the sake of others' pointlessness any more.

name: Night at the Candy Museum - Christmas Work Chair
description: Sit on it and let IDW make all the noise she wants! When you control absolute power, this will be entertainment to you, however detestable it is.

name: Night at the Candy Museum - Biplane of Happiness
description: This biplane of happiness spreads joy all over the world, until the joy in the cabin runs out, and the plane vanishes into the horizon, never to be seen again.

name: Night at the Candy Museum - Honey Mail Basket
description: Every child's letter drips with sweet words so Santa will visit them tonight -- if words are not tools, then they must be murder weapons.

name: Night at the Candy Museum - Sleigh Bench
description: No matter where it goes, take joy in it. The sole secret to happiness is to never wake up.

name: New Year Shrine - Shrine Grounds
description: The wish of this land is that everyone who enters will be barefoot like their Shiba Inus, because there shouldn't be needless division in the world.

name: New Year Shrine - New Year's Clear Skies
description: The sky's wish is that it could be a little shorter and planes could fly a little higher, so it can become closer to this world.

name: New Year Shrine - New Year Mochibana
description: The New Year mochibana's wish is that these biscuits would become real fireworks and blossom, so he can take a long vacation until next year.

name: New Year Shrine - Spring Mochibana
description: The Spring mochibana's wish is that spring won't truly come, so that she can stay here and keep praying for everyone.

name: New Year Shrine - New Year's Kadomatsu
description: The kadomatsu's wish is that its descendants will be uglier, so humans won't display them here.

name: New Year Shrine - Ema Rack
description: The ema rack's wish is that everyone who hangs up emas will do so properly, so as not to block others' wishes.

name: New Year Shrine - Dosojin
description: The dosojin's wish to know who was that girl who held that umbrella for them when it was snowing last week. That snow ended too soon.

name: New Year Shrine - Omikuji -Tying Stand
description: The omikuji-tying stand's wish is for everyone to know that "bad" fortunes are trials that one has to overcome, and that if your luck is too good, it'll only make the fall that much harder.

name: New Year Shrine - Divine Stone
description: The divine stone's wish is for someone to loosen the shimenawa around it, because it ate too many blessings and got fat.

name: New Year Shrine - Zabuton
description: The zabuton's wish is that tomorrow, that father will bring his child here and tell him the ending to that adventure story.

name: New Year Shrine - Shrine Wall - Left
description: The wall's wish is that someday it can turn around and see what the gods it's been protecting look like.

name: New Year Shrine - Shrine Wall - Right
description: The wall's wish is that someday it can turn around and see what the gods it's been protecting look like.

name: New Year Shrine - Maidono
description: The maidono's wish is to be able to someday tell people that out of all the dances it has been offered in the past few hundred years, which shrine maiden is the gods' favorite.

name: New Year Shrine - Sessha
description: The sessha's wish is that people will stuff it with enough money so it can go out and collect chunks of faith!

name: New Year Shrine - Haiden
description: The haiden's wish is for all the people who enter to never give up on their wishes, because what you want to do better reflects yourself than what you actually do.

name: Chinatown - Stone Flooring
description:
Type63: Floors like this really are nicer after all... 
Type64: Yes, I can look down and stare at them all day when the Commander gives a lecture.

name: Chinatown - City Vista
description:
Type59: Oh my...I didn't expect to be able to see something like this. You really are amazing for creating such a stylish landscape. 
Type03: It was made with your hard work too. This is the fruit of everyone's labor, past and present.

name: Chinatown - Big Red Lanterns
description:
Type97: How many years have these lanterns been in use? They're so dirty and tacky... 
Type95: But on Chinese New Year's eve, they're the brightest and most brilliant stars around.

name: Chinatown - Merchandise Stall
description:
Type97S: Tell me the truth, you miser: are you going to sell last year's things to tourists again? 
Type92: Jeez, they aren't trendy anymore so they won't sell this year. I might as well hand them out to everyone as New Year gifts.

name: Chinatown - Tram Car
description:
T65: Next stop, the dessert shop! I came here to bring these cakes home! 
Type81R: I'm sorry, but that shop is run by Type92. Please don't get off here; I'll tell you about a more affordable one.

name: Chinatown - Tram Tracks
description:
Type97S: Chief, have you ever wished that...our tram would never reach the end of the line? 
M99: We will all reach our stop someday, but...there will always be people who keep on going.

name: Chinatown - Chinese Restaurant
description:
Type56-1: Hehe, is it time for me to take the stage? 
Type56R: Remember this - you'll be washing as many plates as you empty, don't you dare run off before that!

name: Chinatown - Traffic Lights
description:
Type80: Come on, just a few more people and I'll be able to cross the road!
Type88: Wait a minute! The light's not green yet, are you trying to crash into the tram?

name: Chinatown - Clock Pailou
description:
JS 9: Why are you so late, 79? Just look at the time up there! 
Type79: Well, uh...I've been training up my "girl power" lately, and being late is an important part of that.

name: Chinatown - Stone Lion - Right
description:
QJY-88: I don't quite get it... What does that look in your eyes mean, T77? 
T77: "These two lions are really cute, can I bring them home with me? I'll ask someone to make them move!" ...We need more bonds, it's really easy to understand.

name: Chinatown - Stone Lion - Left
description:
QJY-88: I don't quite get it... What does that look in your eyes mean, T77? 
T77: "These two lions are really cute, can I bring them home with me? I'll ask someone to make them move!" ...We need more bonds, it's really easy to understand.

name: Chinatown - Red-Leafed Maple Tree
description:
M99: A photo together under the maple tree? Given my height...we might need a selfie stick.
T91: It's okay, I can kneel down. Hold my milk tea... 1, 2! Say cheese!

name: Chinatown - Octagonal Pagoda
description:
NZ75: Why do you only sell these bland clothes in your store? They're not fashionable at all. 
JS05: Hey, if you have a good figure, you'll draw a crowd no matter what you wear.

name: Chinatown - Tram Stop
description: Type81R: The train is about to set off. Welcome to our world, dear friends, and we are also part of your world. May this virtual greeting reach your true heart - I sincerely wish you a Happy Chinese New Year.

name: Chocolatier - Pure White Floorboards
description: The floor is made of white chocolate, so please take off your shoes before setting foot into the room - we can leave our stockings on... Was this your idea, Commander?

name: Chocolatier - Rainy City
description: "I'd give up the world for you" - Ads lie; if you don't love everyone in the entire world, you can't love anyone in it.

name: Chocolatier - Display Case
description: Eat it fast after you buy it, the night won't wait for you. There's no telling whether you or the chocolate will end up melting first.

name: Chocolatier - Payment Counter
description: Do you have a Golden Ticket? ...Huh? A silver one? Congratulations, please pay double the fare and forget everything that happened here!

name: Chocolatier - Grinding Tools
description: Look! We treat cocoa beans so carefully and delicately. Only by exterminating all the savages can the cocoa beans of the entire world know such happiness.

name: Chocolatier - HQ Door
description: Before opening this door, I'm not sure if I'll see a room full of chocolate or walls full of chocolate.

name: Chocolatier - Dessert Fountain
description: Someone once wondered: if cakes don't actually like biscuits, then do chocolates dislike lollipops too? Of course not! But they all seem to be at peace when you look at them!

name: Chocolatier - Sweets Chair
description: The rules are simple - only someone who can eat it all in 15 minutes has the right to sit on it.

name: Chocolatier - Production Apparatus
description: In truth, making real chocolate is an alchemical ritual. When people who truly love each other eat it, they shall gain eternal life - post-apocalyptic consumers will believe anything an ad says.

name: Chocolatier - Mr. Teddy Bear
description: Mr. Bear is pondering the reason for his existence while you are discussing the polite way to eat him. You should eat faster, otherwise he'll melt all over the floor.

name: Chocolatier - Handicrafts Station
description: Making chocolates needs a lot of love - I was talking about heart-shaped molds, not actual love. Put that back, don't let it get cold.

name: Chocolatier - Merchandise Shelf
description: We've got a lot of merchandise beside chocolate, but not all of it is edible. Or perhaps you'd like to buy them all and then try biting them?

name: Chocolatier - Sweet Neon Sign
description: "What a materialistic statement!" A dog in the corner commented on the neon sign.

name: Fairy Market - Medieval Brick Flooring
description: You follow the scent of potions and quickly catch up to the alchemist. "Fine, I'll join you, otherwise the whole town will know what I did to the chickens."

name: Fairy Market - Twilight Forest
description: The witch of the legend is said to live here. Are you willing to befriend her for only a single day? "I'll definitely like you, along with that healthy body of yours..."

name: Fairy Market - Archery Range
description: The condition for recruiting the archer to your party is to beat her in archery. "That is the elven law. But you can also hire me to participate in your place... That is also elven law," she says while shrugging her shoulders.

name: Fairy Market - Haunted Old Castle
description: A rebellious vampire girl has slept here for 495 years... "My beauty sleep really did the trick," says the girl while looking at her own petite body after waking up.

name: Fairy Market - Drengleid Bonfire
description: A suit of immortal armor will occasionally sit by the fire. Holding flames, he looks at you with a hollow gaze. "You got a giant rat? I'll trade myself and my shield for it."

name: Fairy Market - Portable Wine Cart
description: "Where there are drinks, there are warriors. Where there are warriors, there are victories. So the victories you want will depend on how far you can push this wine cart; before we drink every last drop, that is."

name: Fairy Market - Folk House
description: The bard plays his lute while lying on the bed. "A friend of mine died comfortably on this bed. If you can promise me that I can die the same way, then I'll join you."

name: Fairy Market - Folk Street
description: That person is always either running around on your roof or whistling in the grass. "Sorry, my hawk said you look shiny, so I'm here to see if you're a friend...or a target."

name: Fairy Market - Miracle Fountain
description: This fountain is rumored to heal true believers that pray from the bottom of their heart. However, you notice that a cleric is actually the one performing miracles secretly from a corner. "Will you really give me something more meaningful to do?"

name: Fairy Market - Accessory Shop
description: These accessories are useless to you, but you are curious about the shopkeeper's methods. "Buy this ring and I'll tell you where the thief is. Buy this necklace and I'll join your party."

name: Fairy Market - Weapon Shop
description: The weapons sold at this shop are unmatched when it comes to sharpness. The only problem is they break easily. "I look forward to your next visit, and I'm not saying this out of courtesy," says the shopkeeper.

name: Fairy Market - Bright Clouds, Dark Moon
description: This moon is fake. The mage uses it to adjust her sleep or to mess with her nosy sister. "I can slip out whenever. How many dragons did you say there are?"

name: Fairy Market - Sundries Stall
description: "Everything here is clean. I never loot from the dead," said the warlock with a sly smile, "...of course, it doesn't count if they've been resurrected."

name: Fairy Market - Town Bell Tower
description: The paladin saved the town but could not wait in front of the bell tower for the person he loved, so he gave up on the idea of advancing his class and opted to follow you instead. "This is fine. She likes money, but I like myself the way I am now."

name: Classical Concert Hall - Soundproof Flooring
description: Tap-dancing in leather shoes won't make much sound on this specially made floor, but it'll still get you thrown out of the concert hall...

name: Classical Concert Hall - Starry Cyclorama
description: A vault that looks like a starry night sky, but you can't actually see the performers from up here - you can only hear them. Thanks to the obstruction, assassins can easily vanish into the darkness.

name: Classical Concert Hall - Brass Chandelier
description: The candlelight chandelier is apparently the personal choice of the concert hall owner, but those are actually light bulbs due to an accident caused by a loose candle in the past. The blame was shoved onto a certain T-Doll performer known for using incendiary grenades.

name: Classical Concert Hall - Alloy Batten
description: The overhead lights only seem to be there to light up the chandelier. The speakers on the two ends aren't even listed in the inventory. "We aren't speakers! We're amplifiers!" growl the speakers on the rig.

name: Classical Concert Hall - Auditorium
description: The performers only stare at the music sheets in front of them. No one would notice if there are dogs, Sangvis units, or aliens in the auditorium.

name: Classical Concert Hall - Organ
description: It's said that the concert hall has something that used to belong to an old cathedral. For some reason, it keeps reminding people of vampires. The janitors claim to hear music coming from the heavens during nighttime.

name: Classical Concert Hall - VIP Box (Right)
description: VIPs who have paid for more expensive tickets would never sit with whatever it is that sits in the auditorium. Having their own box gives them a sense of superiority as well as minimizes the risk of being assassinated.

name: Classical Concert Hall - VIP Box (Left)
description: VIPs who have paid for more expensive tickets would never sit with whatever it is that sits in the auditorium. Having their own box gives them a sense of superiority as well as minimizes the risk of the common people being assassinated.

name: Classical Concert Hall - Tile Patterned Rug
description: A new product advertised by the manufacturer. It looks like wooden tiles at first glance, but is simply a woven rug. The purpose of such a design is questionable, but the concert hall owner still bought it despite the hefty price.

name: Classical Concert Hall - Spotlights
description: They can create all sorts of dreamy and fantastical effects on the stage, but whenever they're used, the figure on the concert hall electricity meter shoots straight up, warning crew members to save energy.

name: Classical Concert Hall - Percussion Stand
description: The regular percussionist stubbornly insists that a symphony without drums lacks depth, but the audience has grown tired of concerts in which the percussionist bashes her head straight onto the timpani at the very end of a piece.

name: Classical Concert Hall - Stage Chair (Left)
description: The audience will never know what the T-Doll in this seat has gone through. "But now I'm the concert master, so it's all worth it!" says the performer with bruises all over her face.

name: Classical Concert Hall - Stage Chair (Right)
description: Some say that the lower section is less lethal than the higher section. "Forgive me for being blunt, but those kids can't even lift these instruments," says the cellist.

name: Classical Concert Hall - Silent Conducting Stand
description: "I've been working to promote classical music all these years, but a T-Doll brawl that broke out during a concert garnered more attention than everything I've ever done," says the conductor forlornly during an interview after a concert.

name: Jill's Apartment - Old Floorboards
description: Slip-proof and moisture-proof, they possess all the virtues a floor should have. The creaking sound they occasionally make when you step on them is a reminder that you should take good care of the senior citizen in the flooring.

name: Jill's Apartment - Wallpaper
description: A set of wallpaper in plain and ordinary colors. Even if it was made to offset the other items in the room, it hasn't forgotten to add its own unique patterns to the base of the wall.

name: Jill's Apartment - *Kira* Miki Banner
description: A Sashimono or War Banner with *Kira* Miki's face on it. Fills you with fanaticism.

name: Jill's Apartment - Boss's Wall Hanging
description: BEST BOSS - the name says it all.

name: Jill's Apartment - Megachristmas Tree
description: Celebrate the bastardized commercial version of an already bastardized celebration!

name: Jill's Apartment - Kotatsu
description: The kotatsu combines with the two warm traps that resemble floor cushions to produce the legendary cripple-making device. Do not EVER put your legs into the kotatsu, the same way you should NEVER put a lightbulb into your mouth.

name: Jill's Apartment - Cracked Daruma
description: A Japanese souvenir that has seen better days. Still has a vintage charm to it.

name: Jill's Apartment - Light
description: A ceiling light that radiates gentle orange-yellow illumination. Even if you live alone, it can make you imagine that you're warm or comfy.

name: Jill's Apartment - PC-9X
description: It's vintage gaming! Experience the cumbersome load times as they were meant to be!

name: Jill's Apartment - TV
description: Is it a TV or a speaker used to broadcast the background music of life? It is what its user wants it to be.

name: Jill's Apartment - Posters
description: Is there a problem with putting up a grim-looking police mugshot-themed poster beside the female MC of a moe game? Not in this world, at least.

name: Jill's Apartment - Holo-Plant
description: In memory of a real potted plant.

name: Jill's Apartment - Figure Shelves
description: They say the upstairs resident is famous, but according to the residents below, it doesn't matter who's on top as long as the stairs aren't thronged with crazed fans.

name: Jill's Apartment - Joker Cyclone
description: Despite the noisy name, it's just a fan. Fans are good, though. Really good.

name: Jill's Apartment- Open Balcony
description: If this were a real balcony, then opening its doors would let you feel the night wind, and if you were lucky you'd be able to breathe some not-so-stuffy air.

name: Jill's Apartment - Assorted Cartridges
description: They're games that no collector wants, but they're still nice for displaying.

name: Jill's Apartment - Paper Lantern
description: Thanks to the chemical coating preventing bugs from eating it, we advise against using it.

name: Jill's Apartment - Shelf
description: Everything on it was bought cheaply, including the shelf itself. Turning someone else's trash into your personal treasure is also a part of artistic living.

name: Pixel Cafe - Simulated Flooring
description: The simulated wood grain on the hard concrete gives rise to the misconception that you're using plank flooring. Few people will pay too much attention to flaws that they can't see, so if you deceive the eyes, you'll deceive everything.

name: Pixel Cafe - Decorative Wallpaper
description: After putting up this wallpaper, an initially flat wall gains depth, as though the room itself had become bigger. True art allows us to enjoy things beyond our abilities, as this wallpaper elegantly demonstrates.

name: Pixel Cafe - Coffee Bean Storage Jars
description: These jars contain the coffee beans used in the cafe. They're transparent, open and reassuring, and also a way to identify that this isn't a bar, but a cafe.

name: Pixel Cafe - *Kira* Miki Posters
description: Posters of a famous idol. Perhaps it's because she doesn't look too realistic that she's so sought after.

name: Pixel Cafe - Hard Bar Stool
description: These hard bar stools look soft but that's not a lie; they're only that way so the customers can stay lucid at all times. That's right, this place doesn't sell alcohol, but since we're putting on a show, then we have to cover even the smallest details.

name: Pixel Cafe - Emergency Exit Sign
description: Putting a clock in a place where everyone will see it when they enter is a kindness on the part of the cafe owner. It allows social media junkies to know exactly how long they've spent taking selfies.

name: Pixel Cafe - *Kira* Fluorescent Lamp
description: This is an ordinary fluorescent lamp that doesn't quite seem to fit into its environment. However, the name *Kira* allows it to fit seamlessly into its dazzling surroundings. Names really are important, aren't they?

name: Pixel Cafe - Bar Counter
description: There's no rule that cafes can't have bar counters, and there's no rule that counters have to stock alcohol, and there's certainly no rule that the bottles have to contain spirits either. The things which make no sense that you're seeing right now are just decorations. They're not a deception. Definitely not.

name: Pixel Cafe - Real Carpet
description: The best lies are those which contain a hint of the truth in them, which is why we need a real carpet like this. This way, the customers will believe that all the simulated scenery they are seeing is real.

name: Pixel Cafe - Wall-Mounted TV
description: A decoration that automatically plays various ads. Call in if they grab your interest; perhaps you might find a real treasure hidden in the traps of cheapness?

name: Pixel Cafe - No. 9 Projector
description: There is no Projector 1 through 8. It is simply called No. 9, that's all. There doesn't need to be a reason for everything, otherwise there wouldn't be a projector in a cafe without a projection screen in the first place.

name: Pixel Cafe - Gramophone
description: While there are more convenient media for storage and playback, humans still enjoy using such antiquated recording equipment. After its flaws are coated in the dressing known as "history", they transform into what people call "nostalgia".

name: Pixel Cafe - Comic Stand
description: The customers may peruse the manga here for free. If the contents of the manga can draw people, then they can also lead to further drinks being purchased. Don't forget that any kind of customer service is, at its heart, a form of doing business.

name: Pixel Cafe - Pool Table
description: The pixel stylings are just camouflage; the balls can move, and they won't get stuck in the pockets. Relax and play; the only risk you're taking is that you might get thrown out by people who want to drink their coffee in peace.

name: Pixel Cafe - Ventilation Fan
description: Ventilation fans work hard every day, exchanging one kind of stuffy air for another. Perhaps its job is pointless, but its very existence is enough to put people at ease.

name: Pixel Cafe - Pixel Arcade Machine
description: You won't see complex menus and excessive bloom like in other high-end game machines. It is simple and pure, which is why this style is so enduring.

name: Pixel Cafe - Blues Table Set
description: When you sit here, you might feel the need for a whisky and a cigarette. However, this is a cafe; both smoking and drinking are prohibited here. Life doesn't always go the way you want it to, so just sit here and listen to the blues. At least THAT hasn't been banned yet.

name: Pixel Cafe - Cyber Table Set
description: Sitting here won't let you actually reach the digital world, but its name is a lure; under the bewitching radiance of the neon lights, the associations tied to the name "cyber" will guide us to a cyberpunk world.

name: Assembled World - Brick Floorboards
description: Floorboards made of the same material used in manufacturing plastic bricks. Anti-slip, durable and can allegedly withstand the weight of 10,000 jumping T-Dolls - but who'd actually test that?

name: Assembled World - Brick Wallpaper
description: A wallpaper depicting a night view painted in brick style with excellent soundproofing feature. It can keep all gunshots out of the house and maintain a peaceful and quiet atmosphere for inhabitants to enjoy a night of entertainment.

name: Assembled World - Display Cabinet A
description: Only the best of the best has the right to be here. It's an honor, even though it's lonely. The only source of solace is sharing the cabinet with someone interesting.

name: Assembled World - Display Cabinet B
description: Premium products don't wish to be in the display cabinet forever, but there's nothing she can do about it. It's a glorified cage. The one inside wants to get out, the ones outside long to get in.

name: Assembled World - Shopfront Promotional Banner
description: This banner depicting a scene of bliss is the first thing that catches the eye upon entering the room. Don't you envy the girls? Now that you're here, you don't have to - you are in the very same paradise of childhood fun.

name: Assembled World - Brick Lamp
description: The designer has gone with this lamp that looks like an enlarged plastic brick to match the overall décor. One must always shine a light on their dreams.

name: Assembled World - Brick Counter
description: A very basic set of plastic bricks. Their simplicity does not make them any less fun. With enough imagination, one can create extraordinary things out of these ordinary bricks.

name: Assembled World - Pick & Build Wall
description: The wall only provides bricks and parts - no manual, no limit. Everyone yearns for more freedom in life, but only when they're standing at the wall do they realize they need at least a guide to follow.

name: Assembled World - Brick Crane
description: It can be used to move goods and T-Dolls too engrossed in playing with bricks. However, the crane itself was built by a T-Doll who's crazy about bricks. It's a kind of retribution to be picked up and moved by one's own creation.

name: Assembled World - Manticore Display
description: The pride and joy of this shop. The T-Doll who tried to mention the strength of its armor had her mouth clamped shut by her friend - it's better to leave the gunfire behind in a world of toys.

name: Assembled World - Brick Cashier
description: Your wallet suffers in your pursuit of joy. The world is unfair - pain doesn't always guarantee gain, but gain always constitutes pain. At least in here, your joy is guaranteed.

name: Assembled World - New Product Display
description: The seasonal hit is displayed here. Buy a basic set along with the latest product! Don't forget your old friends after meeting new ones.

name: Assembled World - New Product Poster Stand
description: This new product poster stand is replaced every season. Even the best bricks can't be there for you forever. But they don't mind, as long as you never forget how happy you were when you assembled them.

name: Dance Arcade Machine
description: Despite having the heart of a fervent dancer, the Manticore will not share its console with you – a condescending attitude perfectly fits for the jury.

name: Boxing Arcade Machine
description: Don't get mad so easily, and never vent your anger on the machine. Doing so will only teach you a lesson, that your wrath is so pitiful... My lady, stop! Have mercy! I will give you 99/100!

name: Moon Rubbing - Full Moon
description: "An ancient rubbing discovered at the peak of a solitary mountain. It tells the heroic tale of fighting a large beast on this mountain in the age of myths. The stamp is a circle. Specific meaning to be determined."

name: Moon Rubbing - Waxing Crescent
description: "An ancient rubbing discovered near the old lookout. It details the decline of ancient imperial technology. The stamp is a triangle pointing to the southwest. Specific meaning to be determined."

name: Moon Rubbing - First Quarter Moon
description: "An ancient rubbing discovered in the Lost Forest region. It contains information concerning the lost sacred sword and the mysterious tree spirit. The stamp is a triangle pointing to the northwest. Specific meaning to be determined."

name: Moon Rubbing - Waning Crescent
description: "An ancient rubbing discovered in the underwater palace. It contains poems detailing a kind of fantastical creature that guards the underwater cosmos. The stamp is a triangle pointing to the southeast. Specific meaning to be determined."

name: Moon Rubbing - Third Quarter Moon
description: "An ancient rubbing discovered at the campsite outside the city ruins. It reveals the last-known whereabouts of the patriotic dual-wielding warrior as the legendary kingdom fell. The stamp is a triangle pointing to the northeast. Specific meaning to be determined."

name: Moon Rubbing - New Moon
description: "An ancient rubbing discovered at the Demon Hunter Guild HQ. It recounts the tragedy of a female demon hunter who turned into a demon herself due to obsession and ended up being killed by the one she loved. The stamp is a square. Specific meaning to be determined."

name: IIDW
description: Some Dolls enjoy playing on this machine a lot. When you press a key and music comes out, it feels as if a tiny shoot is budding through the soil at the site of an old explosion, smiling at the sky.

name: Singing Weapon
description: It dreams of itself singing as it travels over the hills and plains. In its dream, it doesn't see obstacles being torn to pieces.

name: Aquarium - Floorboards
description: Acrylic floorboards with HD white sand print. May you find the illusion of having a vacation on a tropical island from the fake waves on the floor.

name: Aquarium - Neritic Zone Wallpaper
description: When adventuring in the neritic zone, slow down and try looking for glimmers of light around the shipwreck. Perhaps once you collect 50 antique goblets, you could come out from the top left corner of the screen.

name: Aquarium - Glass Tunnel
description: Your crush is about to leave for Sirius on his mecha, so you plan on showing him the dolphins and confessing your feelings. As you stroll through the glass tunnel, you gaze at his profile and are filled with regret. "If you didn't have to go, or if the world exploded right now, I wouldn't lose you again."

name: Aquarium - Bluegill
description: People are more willing to believe in tall tales than the truth. Bluegills won't die of heartbreak over the death of another bluegill. Who are you kidding? As if a cold-blooded animal would care about the survival of some random fish?

name: Aquarium - Manta Rays
description: Manta rays may look terrifying, and their nostrils and mouth don't actually look like a smiley face, but they're actually a lot nicer than skates - they aren't even venomous.

name: Aquarium - Sea Turtle
description: If you want to ride the currents, a sea turtle is your best bet. However, please take medication to prevent motion sickness or somehow seal your vestibular organ. You won't want to experience puking in the ocean.

name: Aquarium - Whale Shark
description: A whale shark gliding smoothly and slowly, guarding a school of small fish with its large body - this is probably the most tender scene in the ocean. Sadly, all tender things suffer at the hand of destruction - even this giant in the sea.

name: Aquarium - Sawfish
description: "Holding a sawfish makes you the Chainsaw of the Ocean." "That doesn't sound as cool as the Bass of the Ocean." "But can't you hear the bass?" "Alright, I'll be the Chainsaw of the Ocean then."

name: Aquarium - Pink Coral
description: Marine creatures are so fortunate - they don't have to pay five years' worth of tribute to the region they live in; they can move into a beautiful place without having to wait for new properties to enter the market... It's even pink.

name: Aquarium - Golden Coral
description: If you see something gold and shimmery under the sea, don't just assume it's some pirates' treasure and charge straight at it. You might disturb the mermaid couple romancing behind the golden coral.

name: Aquarium - Iron Cage
description: Humans are such lonely creatures. In order to direct attention to the replicas, they even install an iron cage to put themselves in here at the aquarium. Even so, they still get offended when they think they don't have enough attention.

name: Aquarium - Flounders
description: Flounders have had enough of the vast generalization of how one should live their life and the dogmatic definition of success. You could have a successful career, marriage, and education, but your life is more than just having such things. Being able to fearlessly lie on the seabed and rest is a commendable thing that shouldn't be taken lightly.

name: Aquarium - School of Fish
description: To the observers of the world, some creatures are bound to fade into the background. But to some, these insignificant names are enchanting enough to draw them from across an entire ocean.

name: Aquarium - Skate
description: It's trying really hard to make a smiley face with its nostrils and mouth, so why aren't you happy to see it?

name: Nightmare in Room 1408 - Raven Black Floorboard
description: "The floor in this entire department is painted an oppressive, dark color. I can't shake the feeling that there's some brown stuff caked between the gaps..."

name: Nightmare in Room 1408 - Otherworld
description: "The moment I started going up the stairs, everything has changed, but nothing has changed, as if I've crossed into the Otherworld - a parallel or non-parallel plane of existence..."

name: Nightmare in Room 1408 - Sofa of Recount
description: "The exquisite doll spent the whole night telling me stories about her former owner. Whenever it got to an emotional part, the portrait of the former owner started weeping blood..."

name: Nightmare in Room 1408 - Forbidden Elevator
description: "An elevator that has been out of service for years, but some strange hands have clawed open a gap tonight. Thank goodness they won't drag me in asdfghjkl;"

name: Nightmare in Room 1408 - Overloaded Elevator
description: "No matter how long I wait, the elevator display keeps saying it's overloaded. Having run out of patience, I take a peek through the gap...but see only red..."

name: Nightmare in Room 1408 - Swaying Chandelier
description: "There's no wind, but the chandelier keeps swaying back and forth. I hope it won't fall on me..."

name: Nightmare in Room 1408 - Remote-Controlled Tricycle
description: "A tricycle that keeps running back and forth. The person remote controlling it must be a cute kid. Wait...it doesn't have batteries..."

name: Nightmare in Room 1408 - Chef of Midnight Snack
description: "It's just past midnight, and this enthusiastic chef has been pestering me about supper, but I'm honestly not hungry..."

name: Nightmare in Room 1408 - Hide-and-Seek Desk
description: "Heh, kiddo hiding underneath the desk, was it you who typed several dozen pages worth of 'All work and no play makes Jack a dull boy" on the back of my manuscript?"

name: Nightmare in Room 1408 - Meeting at Sunset
description: "My food delivery is finally here! That's weird. Why are they coming through the window? This is the 14th floor, right..."

name: Nightmare in Room 1408 - Masked Maintenance Workers
description: "They claimed to be here to repair the elevator but seemed extremely suspicious. I was just about to make a phone call to verify their identity when I discovered that the phone cable had already been..."

name: Nightmare in Room 1408 - Clown Chair
description: "I finally managed to find some sweets, but the child waiting for me by the chair is gone, leaving only a solitary balloon..."

name: Nightmare in Room 1408 - Bloody Wall of Sighs
description: "The wall is filled with portraits of beautiful young ladies, but the bitter cries and trickling blood make it look like a bad idea to get any closer..."

name: Nightmare in Room 1408 - Stairs Cleaner
description: "She uses her own body as a rag just to clean the stairs. I'm amazed by the quality of service in this apartment block..."

name: Peak Time - Rhombus Tiles
description:
These repeating rhombus tiles, with seemingly no regard for the limits of time and space, have awakened my sense of glory as a god-tier racer."
 "That's just your imagination. Hurry up and finish the tofu delivery."

name: Peak Time - Brick Wall Stickers
description: It looks so retro and stylish you'd never suspect it's applied to cover up a hole.

name: Peak Time - Current Champion
description: It's back once again. This time, it will leave its competitors in the dust. That's right... Only by overcoming your past failure can you have your moment at the apex.

name: Peak Time - McLaren Ultimate
description:
Sitting in one is enough to make both your passenger's and your hearts race.
 That vroom that sounds like a violent storm is recounting its legendary history.

name: Peak Time - Dashing Mini
description:
A car once driven by a certain famous actor. The character he plays is deeply engrained in the hearts of a whole generation.
 Did you watch his show today? That's the only way for you to temporarily escape from the present.

name: Peak Time - Commercial Ceiling Light
description: A good light source is essential to make your collection look radiant. As for the expensive electricity bill...okay, let's just turn on ONE light.

name: Peak Time - Floating Staircase
description:
"Sometimes esthetics and practicality are inversely proportional,"
 say the Dolls queuing to go up the stairs.

name: Peak Time - Motorbike Display Rack
description:
They are waiting for you and you alone.
 Your'e the only one who can rein them in perfectly...not those Dolls who don't even have a driving license.

name: Peak Time - "Pro Racing" Series Helmets
description:
Being a professional takes a lot of passion and just a bit of ambition.
 Well? Try wearing these on the tracks. Show the spectators your passion, ambition...and your sponsor's logo.

name: Peak Time - Photo Collage of Memories
description:
When Dolls see themselves at their peak, they remember those happy times.
 That's the reason why they can put up with the loneliness and find hope on the battlefield.

name: Peak Time - High-Class Coffee Table
description: A coffee table made with high-class materials. You can put some magazines that you like reading, sit down anytime to enjoy... Who took away the chairs?

name: Peak Time - Wall-Mounted Shelves
description: A set of shelves made for categorizing magazines and documents. Once they're classified into... Where did I put last month's expense reimbursement form?

name: Peak Time - Tallinn Landscape
description: Your memory of that battle may fade eventually, but you'll never forget the fate of those T-Dolls.

name: S.F. X'mas Eve - Snowflake Floor
description: While temperature change only has a temporary effect on this marble floor with snowflake patterns, it would cause real snow to melt. "Is this why you're standing on top of me, mourning for snow that has melted?"

name: S.F. X'mas Eve - Silent Woods
description: When Dolls perceive beauty from nature, surely they also sense a certain loneliness. "Please learn from that star and don't disturb the pine trees' dreams."

name: S.F. X'mas Eve - Reindeer that Doesn't Roar
description: This Roarer has been abandoned, but it isn't depressed at all. "I can still be the shield that protects the children who decorate me."

name: S.F. X'mas Eve - Ice Fishing Stool
description: Neither Dolls nor dinergates need to fish for a living, but they still enjoy it as a hobby. A certain dinergate believes that the Griffin demon that it's seen before would say, "I'm trying to prove that inflicting pain and taking lives aren't prerogatives of carbon-based lifeforms."

name: S.F. X'mas Eve - Simulated Ice Fishing Hole
description: When there's what looks like an explorable entrance on the ground, someone is bound to try and see what's inside - even if it's completely empty. "Stop digging! This is a fake water surface created with resin! Don't you speak Drift Ice?"

name: S.F. X'mas Eve - Dinergate's Masterpiece
description: Humans build snowmen, dinergates build snowergates. All intelligent beings enjoy creating things in their own image to alleviate their loneliness. "According to a story written by humans, if I show it enough love, it'll start playing with me!"

name: S.F. X'mas Eve - Boom Gate with Red Light
description: Despite not knowing why humans insist on using this barrier that can't really stop anything as a kind of warning, the S.F. Dolls still honor the tradition and let it do its job. "I know what I'm guarding doesn't matter anymore, but that's not an excuse to leave my post."

name: S.F. X'mas Eve - Argo Covered in Snow
description: When there's no war, weapons lose their purpose. Still, it looks pretty happy - "It's too cold. Let me take a good rest here."

name: S.F. X'mas Eve - Twisted Wire Fence
description: The wire fence stands there stubbornly even though it can't stop truly dangerous enemies. "As long as I can sound the alarm to warn everyone, I'm doing my job."

name: S.F. X'mas Eve - X'mas Tree in Transit
description: The moment the tree gets chopped down, it knows it's going to die soon. So it asks the dinergates, "All trees must die. Could you please return me to the forest after you finish using me? I still want to see the snow next year."

name: S.F. X'mas Eve - Snowy Pine Trees
description: The pine trees invited a star to sit on the treetop to guide lost Dolls home. "Hush, don't tell the star that we're awake. It looks beautiful in its confidence."

name: S.F. X'mas Eve - Restored Junk Heap
description: An ordinary heap of junk that also serves as a trash can when it isn't snowing. But why is Architect laughing so gleefully? "Haha, look! Even the love letter some human wrote to Intruder is replicated here!"

name: S.F. X'mas Eve - Illuminated Fence
description: Destroyer, who never wears night-vision goggles, always crashes into the fence. The pine tree believes that tragedy can be averted simply by having a light installed. It doesn't mind the brightness too much. "Someone has to stay awake and watch over others' sweet dreams."

name: Sleepless City – Sturdy Tiles
description: Due to his obsession with the human foot, he maintains a horizontal position for years and years, but sometimes he just has to stand up for a bit because of the temperature difference.

name: Sleepless City - Miko of the Night
description: She still doesn't understand why people stop calling her Goddess of the Day after she don the vestments of night and neon lights.

name: Sleepless City - River of Mirrors
description: Boats are the ornaments in her hair, the river is her visage. So divine does she look under the lights, all cameras without night mode feel like dying of shame.

name: Sleepless City - Master of Order
description: "I control human traffic in this area to make sure my beloved children don't feel too pressured." as it always says.

name: Sleepless City - Mother of Takoyaki
description: Neither the painful birth that comes with the burning sensation nor the predestined farewell can tarnish the joy she feels as she creates more Takoyaki.

name: Sleepless City - Buildings of Happiness
description: Feel free to ask her for anything you need – you don't have to worry about being rejected. She will grant all your wishes – if you pay.

name: Sleepless City - Hotbed of Culture
description: It's a proven fact that bright things attract crowds – doesn't matter if they're advertizing happy candies or some kind of behavioral art.

name: Sleepless City - Mercurial Skyscrapers
description: The plethora of signboards aren't necessarily beautiful, but they can certainly show you the way to become beautiful. Wanna know why? Shop at IOP Cosmetics!

name: Sleepless City - Origins Plateau
description: Sometimes being bald isn't a bad thing. You can live forever on a signboard, showing your lost successors the way with your shiny head.

name: Sleepless City - Guiding Light
description: Every streetlight that's scared of the dark is burning itself in defiance of the night.

name: Sleepless City - Father of Ramen
description: "All journeys, no matter how long, will eventually come to an end. What you must do is make yourselves more valuable when it ends!" so he teaches every single bowl of ramen he cooks.

name: Sleepless City - Bench of Temporary Refuge
description: He warmly welcomes everything of the past to stay on him, be it people, dust, or rain that has fallen from the sky.

name: Sleepless City - Measurer of Time
description: It marks the passage of time, minding its own business, unaffected by its surroundings. "Really?" the batteries sneer.

name: Sleepless City - Non–Omnipotent Wishing Machine
description: She believes one should always get their money's worth, unless her stock is empty.

name: Snowy Yard - Dark Brick Tiles
description: People will hear a light cracking sound as they walk on this surface, as if the snow and the rocks are whispering to each other - though it's just the effect of thermal expansion.

name: Snowy Yard - Radiant Snow Tower
description: Snow is the most beautiful when viewed indoors. You can enjoy its unblemished purity without being in the cold. The same goes for humans.

name: Snowy Yard - Long-Lived Pine Tree
description: It believes the trees are so tall these days because youngsters are getting better nutrients.

name: Snowy Yard - Moon Pond
description: The water is smooth as a mirror without a single speck. You can do anything you think is elegant and refined here - as long as you don't mind the cold.

name: Snowy Yard - Pavilion
description: "This construction looks like the projector of a Fairy drone..." say the Dolls, who are falling over each other to get a photo in it.

name: Snowy Yard - Buds in Fresh Snow
description: The rocks carefully form a circle to protect the young buds from the sudden blizzard. Still, children are often tougher than you'd think.

name: Snowy Yard - White Marble Stool
description: It stands primly on the ground, pretending there's no graffiti drawn by naughty kids on its belly.

name: Snowy Yard - Bare Hydrangea Tree
description: The tree feels a bit chilly near its crown, but that doesn't make it doubt that spring is only slightly late.

name: Snowy Yard - Veranda of Echoing Footsteps
description: You can sneak up here and watch the plants grow rampantly when they think no one's looking - just like how your homeroom teacher watched you.

name: Snowy Yard - Stone Stool with "Treatise on Superfluous Things"
description: If people don't seek to verify things, they'll never be able to differentiate between genuine and contrived refinement - as just how you won't realize this book is merely a manga wrapped in the cover of an ancient tome if you don't flip through it.

name: Snowy Yard - Stone Table with Chess Endgame
description: QBU-88, I know you mean well, but could you please not reset the chessboard while the Commander and I are halfway through a game? —XM8

name: Snowy Yard - Strange Holey Rock
description: "Constant dripping wears away the stone. Be persistent, and you will succeed." Humans point at the rock to teach their young this lesson even though it's actually artificially created with reinforced concrete.

name: Snowy Yard - New Moon Doorway
description: You probably won't see a different view after passing through it, but perhaps there are those who'll find joy in the passage itself. That's the purpose of an ornamental doorway.

name: Cathedral Lost - Land of Eternal Vows
description: Once upon a time, we lay here, chatting about everything and anything as the gentle morning sun shone upon us. Now, the grass is lush as ever and the sunshine is still tender, but you're no longer by my side.

name: Cathedral Lost - Autumn Woods
description: Countless names are etched onto the tree trunks. The more memorable it was when a name was etched on, the more painful it felt to scrape it off.

name: Cathedral Lost - Hallowed Ray
description: "I promise to love and cherish you forever, till death us do part." I've practiced saying this vow thousands of times, but in the end, I never managed to say it to you.

name: Cathedral Lost - Unlocking Revelations
description: The end isn't always the end. Take this cathedral as an example. Its tenure as a witness to the joys of newlyweds may be over, but its days of collecting tears shed by the old have just begun.

name: Cathedral Lost - Moss-Covered Flower Carriage
description: She once said she didn't like roses as she found them clichéd and tacky. Yet on her wedding day, she smiled so happily riding on someone else's rose carriage...

name: Cathedral Lost - Whispering Ruins
description: Someone once told me that secrets can be buried in tree holes. I couldn't find any tree holes on your wedding day, so I simply buried what I wanted to say to you in a hole in the corner of the wall. A flower somehow bloomed there a few years later.

name: Cathedral Lost - Angel with Misplaced Arrows
description: The moment I met you, Cupid drew his bow and shot a golden arrow into my chest. Only after parting with you did I realize that the arrow is still buried deep in my heart...

name: Cathedral Lost - Holy Grail of Serenity
description: Legend has it that the Holy Grail will grant eternal life to whomever finds it and drinks from it. To someone who is all alone in the world like me, I can think of no crueler punishment.

name: Cathedral Lost - Round Flagstone Patio
description: Round was your lovely smiling face, the moon I beheld with you, the hem of your wedding gown... Now round is nothing but this flagstone patio that we once walked over together.

name: Cathedral Lost - Candlelit Pew (Right)
description: "Go if you want. I can get on with my life without you." What I truly wanted to say was, "Don't go, please stay."

name: Cathedral Lost - Candlelit Pew (Left)
description: "I'm leaving. I don't have a lot of belongings so I'll set off soon." What I actually wanted to say was, "Come with me."

name: Cathedral Lost - Crumbling Pillar with Moss
description: One ordinary day, this pillar collapsed with a mighty crash, just as how one ordinary morning, you walked out of the door and never came back.

name: Cathedral Lost - Double Pillars with Vines
description: These two pillars have withstood the test of time and the profuse growth of vines attest to that. How I wish I could hold your hand and point them out to you right now.

name: Midnight Revelry - Carpet from Milan
description:
It's not just your feet that will feel relaxed, but also your tense mind. Take off your shoes and socks. The satisfaction of stepping on this 1000% softness marks the beginning of a party.
 "If a tree falls in a forest, it obviously makes a sound."

name: Midnight Revelry - Port in Winter
description:
If there's something even more romantic than watching the cold winter night from the warm indoors, then it must be watching it with your friends - we even make bets on which drop of dew is going to drip first.
 "Home is behind, the world ahead."

name: Midnight Revelry - Secret Kingdom
description: Size isn't what matters when it comes to a private space. Even an area of three square inches is enough for stashing your deepest secrets - your dreams, your joys and sadness.

name: Midnight Revelry - House of Friendship
description: Close up the tent and we're the only ones in the world. I have all the things I ever wanted in my life - a sense of security, more sense of security, and the sense of security I feel in your presence.

name: Midnight Revelry - Glowing Leaves
description:
Sometimes there isn't much meaning to the existence of decorations. They are simply there as accessories of a party, and when everything is over, they're the only remaining proof that a joyous celebration has taken place here.
 "It's goodbye. But we look forward to the next crazy venture beneath the skies."

name: Midnight Revelry - Party Leftovers
description: Everyone loves a party, but few appreciate when a party comes to an end. After the bustling excitement, all that remains is a residual warmth, which is actually a bigger and richer source of nostalgia.

name: Midnight Revelry - Couch Potato Heaven
description: Everyone expects me to fight for the future, but all I want is to live my life in peace and quiet. My couch has prepared a surprise party for me; how could I stand it up?

name: Midnight Revelry - Frozen Moment
description:
The best thing about a family theater is that we can watch whatever we want and stop whenever we want.
 "If you want a happy ending, it depends on where you stop the story."

name: Midnight Revelry - Idle Afternoon
description:
Almost everyone wants to do this sometimes - just sitting on the chair, eyes closed, mind blank, doing nothing; not really sleeping, not working either. Just like that. A simple kind of happiness.
 "We toil that we may rest, and war that we may be at peace."

name: Midnight Revelry - Nobody Sleeps
description:
The greatest thing about a pillow fight is that there is never a winner. It's also the only game where no one cares about winning or losing - though perhaps the person who sleeps through the whole thing IS the loser.
 "Life is so interesting. Especially when you think you're better than someone else."

name: Midnight Revelry - Plant of Latent Heat
description: I don't know if the plant is happy that we're laughing and having fun, but I'm guessing it doesn't like noise. "Maybe some noise is exactly what it needs!"

name: Midnight Revelry - Plant of Supercooling
description: I don't know if the plant feels our joy and sadness, but I'm guessing it doesn't like cheesy romance. "Maybe some cheesy romance is exactly what it needs!"

name: Midnight Revelry - Lazy Times
description:
It is our right to find escape in a virtual world, but it's is also our duty to fight in the real world so that we can enjoy our right.
 "Welcome to the real world. It sucks. You're gonna love it."

name: Theater of Splendor - Starlight Floor Tiles
description: The fact is, as long as everything else is glamorous enough, even floor tiles meant for a children's playground will be considered high-class custom-made décor.

name: Theater of Splendor - Mountain View at Night
description: When the lights go out one by one and the hubbub dies down, the stars will come out from behind the neon lights and kiss the mountains within view.

name: Theater of Splendor - I.O.P Theater
description:
Some people make drama out of war; we document war with drama. Which is more horrific – drama that glorifies war or war that rages like drama?
 "However, we'll be showing the Daily Life of Sangvis Dolls today, Commander..."

name: Theater of Splendor - Night Shopping Street
description: This place, like your work, will consume your body and soul and even cost you money, so why don't you consider working overtime instead? As long as you have a job you like, working is actually a more productive form of entertainment.

name: Theater of Splendor - Shopping Arcade
description: All the clothes sold here have a clear price tag to prove that the shop owner isn't as heinous as fate.

name: Theater of Splendor - Innovative Building
description:
Merchants rack their brains to drain your last budget and empty your pockets...
 "Don't put it like that. Market demand is the driving force behind innovation!" says an I.O.P researcher.

name: Theater of Splendor - Event Signature Board
description: Cunning grown-ups invented this thing so that they can graffiti on the wall without getting told off.

name: Theater of Splendor - Y-Shaped Street Lamp
description:
The street lamp is endowed with shiny golden eyes and a tall, slender figure. It is even dressed in a scarlet evening gown... It looks so much prettier than human females, so why don't people like it?
 "Because it isn't a destination that people seek but just a signpost."

name: Theater of Splendor - Sports Car Model
description: It doesn't matter if this is a real sports car or not. After all, guests are only looking for a superficial display that fits their status.

name: Theater of Splendor - Plastic Palm Tree
description: Once the last plants have disappeared, merchants have a reason to promote their own products by degrading real plants, "Look, plastic products are so much better! They can stand tall in cities and ruins alike, forever fresh, forever green."

name: Theater of Splendor - Composite Background
description: Don't be so hung up on authenticity. Who knows, your whole world could be inside a massive film studio. They got the atmosphere right and that's all that matters, don't you think?

name: Theater of Splendor - Road to Success
description: People trample over one another to walk on the red carpet, pretending to be famous film stars. They're no different than the truants who thought they could be top of the class just because they did something.

name: Theater of Splendor - Passers-by and Journalists
description: Can you make the flash any brighter? "Make more noise!" Your colleagues are putting a lot of effort into creating this illusion of grandeur.

name: Lilliput Forest - Grassland of Time
description: A seemingly ordinary patch of grass that actually hides a lot of secrets - sour wood osrrels, dwarf lilyturf bearing round, juicy fruits, and strong-limbed grasshoppers...

name: Lilliput Forest - Forgotten Woods
description: Grown-ups who tarry in these woods will gradually lose their memories - they will forget everything from their adulthood. Even those who kept claiming, "It's just the Tyndall effect!" will end up saying, "I'm catching sunlight that has passed through the leaves in my hands."

name: Lilliput Forest - Teapot Boat
description: A lid-less teapot is drifting on a shallow pond. It is filled with summer cricket-song like a tiny leaf boat.

name: Lilliput Forest - Honey Jars of Somniloquy
description: Every drop of honey envelops an amber-colored dream. If you're curious about these dreams, then listen closely to the soft somniloquy.

name: Lilliput Forest - Chinquapin Tree House
description: No ordinary grown-up can live here. The resident has to counter these sneaky mushrooms and defend against the naughty rascals who keep trying to climb in through the roof.

name: Lilliput Forest - Mole Burrow
description: A pair of eyes are glimmering in the darkness of the burrow entrance hidden just behind the raspberry bush. Don't be afraid, it's just a mole looking forward to some children's visit.

name: Lilliput Forest - Perfect Hiding Spot
description: To children, even the most ordinary rock can mean a lot. For example, this particular rock is the last lifeline when "It" is hot on your heels during an intense game of hide-and-seek.

name: Lilliput Forest - See-Saw Tree Bench
description: To a child, it is the most silent and steadfast listener. To two children, it is the merriest see-saw. Too more than two children, it is the adjudicator of who wins a fight.

name: Lilliput Forest - Woven Vines
description: To prevent children from breaking vines and crash-landing into his house, the owner wove very strong vines into a net and hung it on the branches, but that only served to attract even more little bravehearts...

name: Lilliput Forest - Playing House Hotspot
description: The random bits and bobs scavenged from different homes await their fate quietly while the boisterous children are busy deciding on their final verdict.

name: Lilliput Forest - Mushroom Wonderland
description: Haha, those little devils are finally gone! "We can now play our own games!" "Oh crap, the little devils are back again!" "Hush... Don't move! Pretend we're just simple mushrooms!"

name: Lilliput Forest - Fluttering Butterflies
description: Several butterflies are dancing in the fragrance of flowers. I can't tell if we've intruded upon the butterflies' dream, or vice versa.

name: Lilliput Forest - Kiddie's Little Table
description: This isn't just a flower pot; it's a prison for incarcerating peas. Gosh, these grown-ups always need us to spell everything out for them to understand what the world is like.

name: Zihuatanejo - Blue Waves
description:
When I'm lying at the bottom of the sea, I can't think of any reason to rise to the surface.
 There is beauty in solitude.

name: Zihuatanejo - Uninterrupted Skyline
description:
Someone once told me that the skyline is only five kilometers from me.
 Beyond that is everything, except an end.

name: Zihuatanejo - Port Dreams
description:
If a ship is moored in your dream, where would you want it to take you?
 "I'd like it to take me on a fantastic voyage."

name: Zihuatanejo - Rustling Sand
description: All river currents eventually turn into ocean waves rippling in the tranquil night.

name: Zihuatanejo - Sunset Bar
description: Who doesn't like a drink in the salty sea breeze? Sandwiches, teapots made of tin, gorgeous women, the fading sunset... This is the most beautiful place in the world, 100% guaranteed.

name: Zihuatanejo - Hut of Hope
description: A small hut and some worthless old boats. Perhaps I could get some rest here, not busy living, nor busy dying. I will count the sunsets and the waves, thinking neither of the past nor the future.

name: Zihuatanejo - Sea-Facing Pier
description: To you, this might just be a brief stop in your life, but to them, this is a warm den.

name: Zihuatanejo - Kingdom in the Isle
description: In an ocean with no memory, the most valuable treasure is this piece of land. Facing the sea in all directions, I am the king of this place.

name: Zihuatanejo - Marine Neighbors
description: On an island, your only neighbors are the fish and shrimps swimming in the water. Some of them stay behind, while some swim on.

name: Zihuatanejo - Tropical Palm Tree
description:
You planted a palm tree when you first arrived. Now that it's fully grown, you must give it the space it needs.
 Time always leave behind marks when you least expect it.

name: Zihuatanejo - Palm Tree Cluster (Left)
description: These friends who shield you from the sea winds are the anchor of your safe and peaceful life. There are always those around us who suffer through everything in silence.

name: Zihuatanejo - Palm Tree Cluster (Right)
description: These friends who shield you from the sea winds are the anchor of your safe and peaceful life. There are always those around us who suffer through everything in silence.

name: Zihuatanejo - Fish Bone Signpost
description:
Why do I have a signpost even though it's my home?
